title: nicole keeling's chess cake
directions: Mix together; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gelatin salad(carrot-celery-olive)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add vinegar and ice cubes. Stir constantly until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.

title: non-boozey raspberry daiquiris
directions: Put in a handful of ice cubes and blend ingredients until "slushy."

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream
together the butter, eggs and sugars until light and fluffy.
Sift together the baking powder, soda and flour. Stir into creamed mixture until well blended.
Fold in chocolate
and raisins
or
nuts.	Drop
by teaspoons onto greased baking	sheets and bake at 350° for 7 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook together, drain and mash the squash, onion and carrots. Mix together soup and sour cream, then add to mashed mixture.
Put layer of stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then a layer of squash mixture.
Next, drizzle butter over.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned syrup cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add to oil and sugar gradually.
Add flour gradually and mix well. Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add peanuts and pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Quickly form into 1 1/2-inch balls. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Take chicken and remove bones.
Take chicken and soy sauce in skillet and brown.
Put celery and onion in large pot.
Cook until tender, then add chicken.
Cook until flavors are cooked in then add cornstarch and sorghum.
Put bean sprouts last and cook four minutes.
Add chicken broth to pot.
Add chow mein noodles on top.

title: uncle aub's chocolate ice cream
directions: Heat sugar, cocoa, eggs and a little milk, enough to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining milk.
Put in ice cream mixer and freeze.

title: baked chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Place in baking dish and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: favorite banana pudding
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler; stir in brown sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly (15 to 20 minutes).

title: meat and broccoli strata
directions: With a 3-inch cookie cutter, cut a design out of each bread slice; set aside.
Tear remaining bread into pieces, place in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer with sliced cheese, broccoli, meat and bread cutouts.
In a medium bowl, beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: rice pudding(top of stove)
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork until thoroughly blended.
(I put this back into the bread crumb container and refrigerate until needed.)

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Chop onion and pepper and saute in margarine.
Add beef and cook until done.
While cooking beef, separate with a fork. Combine all other ingredients.
Layer cheese and Fritos on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: white cake
directions: Mix following directions on package, using the milk instead of water and 3 egg whites instead of 2.
Bake according to package directions.

title: beans ... and(low sodium)
directions: Brown diced pork in a large skillet with chopped onion, garlic, onion powder and seasonings.
Add brown sugar, celery and pineapple.
Simmer over low heat until ready to serve or place in oven casserole at 325° to 350° or crock-pot.

title: sunrise pancakes
directions: Prepare Vanilla Cream Syrup; set aside.

title: chewy molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs and molasses; mix well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield: approximately 8 dozen cookies.

title: sausage spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti; drain.
In skillet cook hot links and pepper until pepper is tender-crisp.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: fat-free banana bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° in loaf pan for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add dry ingredients and chill dough.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in mixture of 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until very light brown.
Cool slightly before removing to cooling rack.

title: california raisin sauce
directions: Rinse raisins; add water, jelly, rind and juice and bring to boil.
Blend sugar with cornstarch, salt and allspice; stir into orange mixture.
Cook, stirring, until clear.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Great for baked ham.

title: upside-down pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter, sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Add enough milk to make a batter; beat 1 minute. Pour into a buttered casserole. Make topping by using pineapple mixed with remaining sugar. Bring to a boil. Pour over batter. Bake in 400° oven 30 minutes. Serve hot or cold. Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Crush chips and put half in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Combine soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and broth.
Whisk until smooth.
Pour half over chips in pan. Sprinkle chicken, onion and cheese over soup in layers.
Put another layer of chips, soup, chicken, onion and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and cheese melts.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease casserole with margarine using 1 (12 x 7 x 2-inch) dish. Arrange 6 slices of bread in the bottom of baking dish.
Cover with the cheese, then with the remaining bread.
Beat the eggs; add the milk, mustard, onion, salt, pepper and Accent.
Pour over the bread.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° to 1 hour.
Serve immediately or cover casserole and refrigerate overnight and bake the next day.

title: mexican beef noodles
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef and 1/2 cup chopped peppers and 1/2 cup chopped onion; drain.
Add 2 cups of water and 1 bag Lipton beef noodles.
Cook on medium heat for 7 minutes.
Add 1 can of kernel corn, drained, and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil margarine and brown sugar for 2 minutes.
Set off heat. Add milk and return to heat.
Let come to rolling boil.
Cool to lukewarm and beat powdered sugar in mixture.
Beat until smooth consistency to spread on cake.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Place
turkey
slices
in
shallow
oblong baking dish. Arrange asparagus spears on top.
Mix steak sauce and soup and pour
over asparagus.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven
at
for about 20 minutes, then place under broiler until bubbly.

title: key lime pie
directions: Place
the condensed milk, cream cheese, lime juice and vanilla in	a
food processor or the large bowl of an electric mixer.
Blend
on
medium
speed
for
minutes.
(The long mixing
time
incorporates	air
and
eliminates lumps.) Place filling in	the cooled, baked crust and refrigerate at least 8 hours
before
serving.
Garnish
with fresh whipped cream and twisted lime slices, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: saucy oven barbecue steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut into serving size pieces.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add steak; brown on both sides.
Transfer steak to a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Combine ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over steak.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: canned peach filling
directions: Slice peaches; add sugar and lemon juice to peaches.
Mix and let set while cooking glaze.
Bring peach juice concentrate and 5 cups water to a boil.
Dissolve rest of water in clear jel and thicken boiling juice, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add salt, butter and almond extract.
Add peaches to cooked glaze.
Fill canning jars and process.
I pressure can at 5 pounds for 5 to 10 minutes and invert cans to help them seal.
Yields 8 1/2 quarts.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Sterilize the jars for 5 minutes.
Wash pickling cukes. Let stand in
water
for
hours.
Put
sprigs of dill in bottom of	quart
jar.
Pack
cukes
in
jar.
Add 2 pieces of garlic and a
piece
of red pepper.
On top of each jar, put 2 sprigs of dill and a sprinkle of alum.
Combine vinegar, salt and water and bring
to a boil.
Fill jars and seal.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: linguini with feta peppers
directions: In medium bowl, pour boiling water over tomatoes to cover for 2 minutes.	Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Thinly slice tomatoes and set aside.

title: tuna and white bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix gently.
Keep chilled until serving time.
Mixture can be served in lettuce cups, hollowed out tomatoes or on toast or an open face sandwich.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, 1 teaspoon brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add egg and beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix just until blended.

title: weight watchers salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Keeps 7 days in refrigerator.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix the boiling water and jello well.
Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add to the jello mixture with the lemon juice.
Add the vanilla and mix well.
Whip the chilled Carnation milk and fold into other mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Sprinkle remaining crust over top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Heat oil and brown flour.
To the 2 c. water add the chili powder and disolve.
Add the mixture to the browned flour and mix well.
Add seasonings and blend.
Bring it to a bubb boil, stirring frequently.
Simmer covered for 5 min.
Evaporated milk can be added to soften flavor.

title: ham roll-ups(children's)
directions: Place one cheese slice and one broccoli spear on a ham slice. Roll up and hold together with toothpicks.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Mix soup and milk in a bowl.
Pour soup and milk mixture over ham rolls.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta and vegetables
directions: In large saucepan, prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Add carrots, broccoli and pepper for the last 5 minutes of cooking time; drain.

title: wild rice and seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: turkey tortilla casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery; add broth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until veggies are tender.
In a large bowl, stir together undrained onion mixture, turkey, tortillas, chili peppers, soup and black pepper.
Reserve 1/2 cup each cheese.
Stir remaining cheeses into mixture.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with salsa and remaining cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding, milk, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Alternate wafers, bananas (sliced) and pudding mixture.
Garnish with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: ma murphy's pea soup
directions: In a large kettle, melt margarine.
Add celery, onion and bone.
Saute until onion and celery are tender.
Add water, peas and pepper.
Simmer, covered, until peas mash between fingers (about 1 hour).
Remove bone from kettle; cut off meat and reserve.
Add hot milk and meat; do not boil.
Ready to serve.
If too thick, you may add more milk.
Serve with croutons, if desired.

title: barbecued kielbasa
directions: In a medium saucepan, put catsup, brown sugar, onion, liquid smoke and garlic powder.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Put kielbasa in a casserole dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until kielbasa is completely heated through and barbecue sauce thickens up.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt chocolate over boiling water.
Add milk; stir 5 minutes, or until thickened.
Add water; mix well.
Pour into freezing tray.
Freeze until ice crystals form around side of pan.
Add vanilla and whipped cream until thick enough to hold a soft peak. Fold into chilled mixture and freeze.
When half frozen, scrape from sides and bottom of tray.
Beat until smooth, but not melted. Freeze until firm.

title: cheddar vegetable squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Chop onion.
In large frying pan, heat the oil over medium heat.
Add onion, cover, cook until tender (about 5 minutes).
Add frozen vegetables, marjoram, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Cook until tender, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes. Meanwhile, grate cheese.
Beat eggs with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Transfer vegetable mixture to a bowl.
Stir in Bisquick, 1 cup of cheese and the egg mixture.
Transfer to baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut boiled eggs in halves (each).
Put yellow in bowl separately.
Arrange on pretty tray.
Break up yellow with fork. Add salad pickles, about 1 tablespoon of mustard and enough Miracle Whip to reach a creamy fluffy consistency.
Generously fill whites.
Any leftover yellow mixture makes a great sandwich (smile).

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tops and bottoms off of tomatoes and make slices approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and lightly dip in flour.
Fry in hot butter until brown on both sides.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans well using juice.
Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300°
for 45 to 60 minutes.
These pies freeze well.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix as directed on package and then add drained corn.
Pour half of mixture into an 8 x 8-inch greased dish.
Then evenly spread meat over mixture.
Then spread cheese on.
Add remaining mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Let apples and sugar stand in a mixing bowl while you beat 2 egg whites until stiff. Then add yolks and stir. Add oil to egg mixture. Beat well and let stand. Mix together flour, baking soda, salt, pecans and cinnamon. Pour egg mixture over apples. Stir, then add dry ingredients. Stir with a spoon. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix up all ingredients and freeze.
Take out of freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat bacon drippings in deep pan (I use iron skillet).
Add cabbage, onion and salt. Cover and cook slowly for about 20 minutes, stirring often. Add sugar and cayenne pepper to vinegar and mix well.
Pour over cabbage and cook for 5 minutes longer.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High for 5 minutes. Stir and serve with nacho chips.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Beat until light and fluffy. Add 7-Up and beat well again. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan. Bake about 40 minutes or until done. Remove from oven and immediately cover with Icing.

title: parmesan onion canapes
directions: Mix cheese with mayonnaise.
Make small rounds of thin sliced bread; spread with mayonnaise mixture.
Place a very thin slice of onion on each.
Put 1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise mixture on top of onion and sprinkle top generously with Parmesan cheese.
Put canapes on cookie sheets in refrigerator until ready to use.
Broil in preheated oven until golden brown.
Watch closely as these burn easily.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes; gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture. Spread on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel (not terry one) sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together; cool. Unroll and take off towel.

title: traditional sweet roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: steak house grilled sirloin
directions: Mix steak sauce, onion, garlic and pepper sauce; set aside. Grill or broil steak until desired doneness, brushing with sauce mixture occasionally. Makes 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Add melted chocolate. Put in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: surprise cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Use 2 small cake pans. Cool and slice each cake to make 4 layers.
Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Use this mixture to put layers together.
Frost top and sides of cake with Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies or bars
directions: Spread dough in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: creamed corn
directions: Take a knife and slice through each kernel of corn.
Then in a large bowl and with the same knife, push off all the corn into the bowl.
Place corn in a pan with butter, milk, salt and pepper. Cook on low, stirring regularly to keep it from sticking.
Cook between 45 to 60 minutes.

title: jade empress chicken
directions: Combine the sherry, soy sauce, ginger and garlic in a bowl. Place the chicken cubes in the mixture and marinate in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
In a large skillet bring the stock to a boil.
Add the mushrooms and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add the celery, onions and green pepper and stir-fry an additional 2 minutes.
Stir in the chicken and marinade and cook until the chicken is opaque, about 2 minutes.
Drain the pineapple, reserving the juice, and cut the chunks into thirds, setting them aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put cooked, deboned chicken breasts (cut up) in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Mix soups, broth, margarine and drained peas and carrots.
Pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick and milk (it will be thin).
Spoon over chicken mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into paper lined muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: "easy" mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into lightly greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lettuce-cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a large bowl.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Toss well at serving time.

title: crock-pot greens and corn bread
directions: Cook greens down in crock-pot. Fix corn bread batter, then pour over greens. Cover and cook until corn bread is almost done. Cover and simmer until done.

title: easy homemade pickles
directions: Combine in a saucepan the sugar, vinegar, crushed stick of cinnamon, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to boiling, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over pickles which have been cut diagonally crosswise in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Add half of garlic clove.
Set in refrigerator for 1 week before serving.

title: baked grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package directions!
Add cheese, butter and eggs.
Pour into baking pan.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter, butterscotch morsels and chocolate morsels in double boiler over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill until firm.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: appetizer cheese roll
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, olives and chilies in medium bowl.
Place room temperature Velveeta cheese between two layers of Saran Wrap or waxed paper. Roll into rectangle until about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread mixture evenly over Velveeta.
Using bottom paper, roll into log.
Place on serving dish seam side down.
Trim ends evenly.
Place in refrigerator, covered, for at least three hours.
Serve with different types of crackers.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Wrap a salted soda cracker with a piece of bacon and secure with a toothpick (1/2 slice per cracker).
Bake on a rack on a cookie sheet in a slow oven until brown and bacon is crisp. Remove toothpick while warm.
Can be frozen and then placed in oven to just warm before serving.

title: spicy texas trash
directions: Add to margarine mixture, stirring well after each addition. Bake at 200° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: overnight rump roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Cut garlic clove in half and rub garlic on each side of roast.
Cover all sides of roast with flour.
Brown floured roast in oil on both sides.
Place roast in slow cooker. Add onion soup mix, golden mushroom soup and 1 soup can of water to pan the roast was browned in.
Bring to slow boil.
Stir well and pour over roast.
Cook overnight on high.

title: veal kabobs on the grill
directions: Mix
oil,
lemon
juice,
soy and Worcestershire sauce, seasoning salt
and pepper.
Marinate veal in mixture for 3 to 4 hours.
Skewer veal cubes alternately with mushrooms, green peppers,
tomatoes	and
onions.
Cook
on	outdoor grill over medium coals, turning occasionally and brushing with marinade. Serve with wild rice.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in egg, vanilla and salt; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in slightly cooled chocolate. Frosts top and sides of 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: golden cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat egg yolks well and add to mixture, creaming thoroughly.
Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to batter alternately with milk, scraping sides of bowl frequently.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.

title: homemade pimiento cheese
directions: Grate cheese (the whole box, depending on amount desired) on cutting board, then put grated cheese in plastic serving bowl. Then add pimiento and salad dressing until it is creamy enough. When halfway stirring salad dressing into cheese and pimientos, add pickle juice.
Then continue stirring until it's ready to serve.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell and cool.
Wash strawberries and drain, removing caps.
Place 2 layers of whole berries in pie shell with pointed ends up and largest berries in the center.
Prepare glaze.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix meat with 1/2 can tomato sauce and remaining ingredients. Set remaining sauce aside.
Shape meat into loaf and place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Drain.
Pour reserved tomato sauce over meat loaf and bake 5 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab treats
directions: Cream the cheese and oleo, then stir in seasonings.
Use a fork to flake the crab meat and stir into cheese mixture.
Spread mixture on all 48 muffin pieces, placing on cookie sheets and freezing.
Package and keep frozen until needed.
May also be baked without freezing.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly. Good as a snack or served with salad or raw vegies.

title: randy's green bean surprise
directions: Mix beans and soup in casserole dish.
Bake until center is hot.
Sprinkle with potatoes on top and bake another 10 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: lite fruit cooler
directions: Drain the fruit and combine with the cottage cheese and Cool Whip in a medium mixing bowl.
Sprinkle the jello over the top and stir to mix well.
Add pecans, if desired.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Fry bacon and place on paper towel.
Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon drippings.
Drain drippings and add remaining ingredients to pan.
Crumble and add bacon.
Cook on medium to low heat until cheese is melted.

title: baked chicken and cheese
directions: Put chicken in a layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with layers of Swiss cheese.
Combine 1 can of soup with milk and spread over chicken and cheese.
Top with dressing.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Cover with foil at end of baking time if dressing starts to get too brown.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Then add coconut and nutmeats.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine thawed potatoes, 1/2 cup oleo, onion, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Place in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix crushed corn flakes and the remaining 1/2 cup margarine and spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish and serve hot.

title: "little challahs" bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in ginger, salt and sugar. Blend in flour.
Stir until moist.
Knead on floured board until smooth.
Break into 12 to 14 pieces.
Roll into ropes (3) and braid.
Arrange on lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Brush with egg. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator. Good on apples.
Soak apple slices in orange juice to keep from turning dark.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Make batter out of flour, shortening, salt, sugar, soda and buttermilk.
Pour into baking dish.
Heat fruit of your choice with sugar to taste.
Pour hot fruit on batter.
Bake slowly at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: turnip greens
directions: Put greens and turnips in large pot. The greens cook down but to begin, you will need to push them down to get all into the pot. Boil until tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Season with bacon drippings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions and cook slowly for 15 minutes, covered.
Uncover, increase heat to moderate and cook about 35 minutes, stirring frequently and scraping bottom of pan until onions are deep golden brown.
Sprinkle with salt and flour and stir for 3 minutes.
Stir in broth and simmer, partially covered, for 35 minutes.
Toast bread slices.
Place toast in individual bowls.
Pour soup over toast and sprinkle with cheese (melt cheese in microwave).

title: sausage eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake
in 8-inch square pan for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sausage and egg breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together eggs, mustard, salt, milk and green chilies. Cook and drain sausage.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer ingredients as follows.
First 5 slices white bread (cubed), 2nd sausage, 3rd egg mixture and 4th grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: spud burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a roll.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven or on charcoal grill, basting with steak or barbecue sauce as desired.
Slice for burgers.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Pop the corn and mix with nuts on cookie sheets.
Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking and stir occasionally for 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns light caramel color.
Pour over corn and nuts and mix.

title: apple nut pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar.
Beat eggs slightly; blend in oil and vanilla.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Turn into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until cake is golden brown and springs back when touched lightly.

title: navajo fried bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make well in middle.
Slowly add liquid and mix in from center.
Dough should be slightly sticky.
Let set; wait 1 hour.
Take small ball; roll or pat out very thin.
Drop in smoking Crisco or oil.
(Make sure it's hot.)
Turn when golden brown.
Drain on paper.
Serve warm or keep hot in warm oven. Serve with chopped lettuce, onion, tomatoes, shredded cheese and taco sauce.

title: garlic roasted chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice, garlic powder, seasoning salt and pepper.
Wrap chicken loosely in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place chicken in ovenproof dish and bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O in bowl with 1 pint of hot water. When mixed well, add sugar, then add cold water. Stir in remaining ingredients, except ginger ale. Add ginger ale just before you serve.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil rice in salt water until tender.
Remove desired amount of leaves from cabbage and chop.
Place leaves in pot with enough boiling salt water to cover and add vinegar; let simmer.
Boil 5 minutes until done.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press dough flat on lightly greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Cut into squares.
Top with any or all of the following:
cherry tomatoes, cucumber, radishes, olives, mushrooms, onions, celery, bacon, sprouts, green pepper, carrots, cauliflower, shrimp, broccoli and cheese.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape int good size thick cakes.
Fry in butter or margarine until brown.
Makes 2 to 4, depending on how thick you like them.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Cook mushrooms, green pepper and onions until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add chicken and pimento. Heat just to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sherry. Spoon chicken mixture into patty shells or over toasted muffins or toast.
Yields 4 cups.

title: chicken, sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Saute sausage and set aside.
In drippings, saute mushrooms and onions; add sausage and cooked chicken.
Cook wild rice according to package directions.
In separate pan, mix flour with cream until smooth.
Add broth and cook until thickened.
Add seasonings along with the rice, sausage, chicken, mushrooms and onions.
Put in 10 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add onion and remaining ingredients.
Cook well.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Yields 12 servings.

title: green chile chuck roast
directions: In deep skillet or Dutch oven, heat oil hot.
Brown roast on both sides.
Add onion and chilies, turn roast to cover fully with onion and chilies.
Pour beer around side of roast.
Sprinkle with seasonings and cover with tight lid.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours over low heat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix egg and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add flour, oil, milk, baking powder and salt by hand.
Stir well.
Stir in flavorings and poppy seed.
Pour mixture into loaf pans which have been prepared with margarine and sugar.
(No flour).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "the beacon" barbecue
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Simmer all other ingredients together for 30 to 45 minutes or until slightly thick, then add shredded meat.
Cook together for a few minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain.
Drain carrots.
In mixing bowl add undiluted soup, mayonnaise and egg and mix well.
In casserole dish (large one) put broccoli and carrots in.
Pour mixture over top; spread (do not stir in).
Place shredded cheese over the top. Top with bread crumbs and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Season hot potatoes with butter, cinnamon and nutmeg to taste. Add corn flakes and sugar.
Shape into balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill at least 30 minutes or overnight.
Arrange on pineapple slices in buttered baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half and wrap with bacon slice. Put the beef in an 8 x 10 inch baking dish. Place chicken on top of beef. Mix together the sour cream and the soup and pour over chicken. Cover pan and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Remove cover during last 20 minutes of baking.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Blend orange juice concentrate (undiluted) and Worcestershire sauce in blender.
Do not add any other ingredients.
Marinate chicken pieces about 1 hour.
Cook over low flames, turning occasionally and basting often with marinade.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix molasses, sugar, water, vinegar and butter.
Cook over medium heat in cast iron skillet until it cracks in cold water. Add soda and stir for a minute.
Pour mixture over popped corn and allow to stand until cool.
In palm of hands (with butter on them) press together into balls.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add eggs.
Then add soda added to buttermilk and vanilla.
Use enough flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out.
Use a 450° oven.

title: soy sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients; boil gently, uncovered, 5 minutes, until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Chill to store; stir before using.
This sauce has 120 mil. of sodium per teaspoon.

title: a wilson special
directions: Peel and wrap the banana tightly in plastic wrap. Put it in the freezer for 2 hours. Place yogurt, strawberries, banana and orange juice in the jar of a blender. Puree until smooth and frothy.

title: cheese and ham quiche
directions: Mix together cheese, eggs, half and half, paprika, pepper, salt and ham.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set and brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Place chicken in dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, garlic, and onion powder to taste. Add soy sauce to juice from pineapple and mix.
Baste chicken with mixture.
Pour pineapple over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. (When using boneless chicken bake for 30 minutes)
Serve over rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 2 quart greased casserole dish.
Pour water or orange juice over the apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of apples. Mix flour, brown sugar and butter. Put on top of cinnamon apples. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix well.
Place in a greased 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until it feels firm.
Cut in squares and serve with cream of chicken or cream of mushroom soup on top.

title: coffee-orange-fudge cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips and confectioners sugar.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Add chips and blend.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies(diabetic)
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen sugarless chocolate chip cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shoestring snack
directions: Pre-heat oven to 450°.
Spread potatoes evenly on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat about 4 minutes. Serve while hot.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Add boiling water and stir until dissolved. Cool. Add lemon juice, pineapple (with juice) and sugar.
Chill until partially set. Combine half Cool Whip with mixture.
Line a large bowl with plastic wrap. Break up cake into bite size pieces and alternate layers of mixture with cake layers. Refrigerate until firm (overnight).
Unmold cake and frost with remaining whipped topping. Sprinkle generously with coconut.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Place dough on a cookie sheet (over wax paper).
Sprinkle nuts.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven on a greased cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Prepare a hand or dish towel (clean) with powdered sugar.
Place dough on towel.
Place in the freezer for 5 minutes.

title: spinach, red pepper, and feta quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: savory pork-vegetables
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chops for 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove.

title: shortcut strawberry cake
directions: Butter the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread the miniature	marshmallows
evenly
over
the
bottom.
Combine strawberries, syrup and dry gelatin.
In a large bowl, combine the rest
of
the ingredients.
Blend and beat for 3 minutes. Spoon the batter over
the marshmallows, then spoon the strawberry mixture over the batter.
Bake
for
to 50 minutes. Serve hot, warm or	cool
with
ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cooked mayonnaise
directions: Beat egg yolks together with sugar, salt, mustard, red pepper and Wesson oil.
Set aside.
Mix water and vinegar and beat until it comes to a boil.
Beat water and vinegar into the first mixture.
Put entire mixture in top of a double boiler and cook until it is thick.
Pour into a covered jar and keep in refrigerator.

title: spanish rice in microwave
directions: No spires miraculously arise,

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; slice crosswise into 1/4 inch slices.
Soak in buttermilk at least 20 minutes.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip eggplant into flour.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: pumpkin cloud pie(sugar-free)
directions: In a medium bowl, stir cream cheese with a spoon until soft. Add 1/2 cup Cool Whip free and coconut extract. Mix gently to combine. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, dry pudding mix, dry milk powder and water. Mix well using a wire whisk. Blend in pumpkin pie spice and remaining 1/4 cup Cool Whip free. Spread half of mixture into pie crust; evenly spread cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over top. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Cut into 8 servings.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket in oblong baking dish; sprinkle with liquid smoke and salts.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Place foil loosely over meat.
Cook at 275° for 5 hours.
Uncover and pour barbecue sauce over meat.
Cook without foil for another hour.
Remove to platter and let cool before slicing.
Remove fat from sauce remaining in dish.
Add flour and water to sauce and stir.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Serve sauce hot with meat. Serve with rice or potatoes and tossed green salad.
Makes 10 servings.

title: maria's pineapple punch
directions: Take a quart of water and bring to a boil.
Stir Jell-O and sugar until dissolved.
Place mixture in gallon container.
Fill container to 2 inches from the top with water.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer and let thaw to a slush.
Add pineapple juice and ginger ale to punch bowl.

title: cherry-o-cream pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla in a blender on medium speed.
Add cream cheese while blender is running, 1 piece at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into pie crust; top with filling.
Refrigerate until firm and serve.

title: doug's chili
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef, onions and green pepper until vegetables are tender; drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, salt, chili powder and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove the bay leaf.
Serve piping hot.

title: the next best thing to robert redford #2
directions: Crust:
Combine pecans, flour and butter.
Mix together; press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandmother burgess' vanilla ice cream
directions: In double boiler, scald milk.
Mix next 4 ingredients; stir in enough milk to make smooth paste.
Stir into rest of milk in double boiler.
Stir until thickened.
Cover and cook 10 minutes. Cool.
Add vanilla and cream.
Freeze in 2-quart freezer until hard to turn, using 8 parts crushed ice to 1 part ice cream salt. Makes 1 1/4 quarts.

title: garlic barbecue dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a jar with a tight-fitting lid and shake well.
Refrigerate overnight or longer, the longer the better.
Baste meat several times while cooking.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Stir flour, oats, gumdrops, baking powder, soda and salt and set aside.
With mixer, cream margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in egg and stir in flour mixture.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour.
Add to sugar and eggs.
Add pineapple and juice; mix well.
Add chopped walnuts. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 3-inch ungreased pan.
Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Gradually add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cake.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil, eggs and water in mixer bowl; mix well.
Stir in bananas and pecans.
Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar, beet juice and cornstarch. Simmer until thick.
Add beets and butter.
Cook until beets are hot through.

title: apple oatmeal bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices in large bowl.
Stir in brown sugar, oatmeal and walnuts.
Combine eggs, milk and butter. Add to oatmeal mixture.
Add apples but do not overmix.
Spoon into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into middle comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out of pan.
Cool completely and wrap.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut rolled cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices; line pizza pan with slices until covered.
Bake according to package directions.

title: tortellini minestrone soup
directions: Get out a very large bowl.
Shred the cabbage by hand, or in a food processor and place in bowl.
Add the diced tomatoes, sliced onions and diced cucumbers.
Add both cans of sliced beets, including all the beet juice.
Add olive oil, salad oil and vinegar.
Next, add oregano, sweet basil leaves, sugar, salt and black pepper.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: In saucepan, beat eggs with sugar, Pet milk and 2 cups regular milk.
Cook until pudding consistency.
Cool.
Add Eagle Brand milk, vanilla, 3 bananas, jar of maraschino cherries plus 1 tablespoon cherry juice, pineapple, pecans and food coloring to desired color.
Finish filling can with milk and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Use to baste pork when grilling.
Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: tossed vegetable salad
directions: Wash thoroughly the greens, cut up in pieces.
Slice cucumber and onion.
Cut pepper in thin 1-inch slices.
Peel avocado and cube.
Toss in all ingredients, including chickpeas.
Chill.

title: mom's butter bean soup
directions: Put butter beans in water to about 3 times depth of beans; add pork and onion.
Cook until beans are tender.
If needed, add water during cooking.
When beans are tender, salt and pepper to taste and add chili sauce.
At this point, depending upon meat you chose, you may want to shred bits into soup or serve for sandwiches on side.
Simmer now about 15 to 20 minutes.
Hearty, inexpensive and easy!

title: oatmeal chewies
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine oats, 1 1/2 cups of flour, brown sugar, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in margarine; mix until well blended.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining onto a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.
Mix caramel and 1/4 cup of flour until smooth (easier if warmed slightly).
Drizzle over nuts and chocolate pieces to within 1/4 inch of pan edges.
Sprinkle with reserved mixture. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: macaroni, cheese and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Put 1/2 in casserole dish.
Slice up half of Velvetta cheese and layer on macaroni.
Put 1 1/2 cans chopped tomatoes in layer on top of cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbles, approximately 25 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Slice unpeeled orange into eighths; remove seeds.
Place half the cranberries and half the orange pieces in a food processor container.
Process until mixture is evenly chopped.
Repeat with remaining cranberries and orange pieces.
Stir in sugar to desired sweetness.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Delicious with Thanksgiving turkey!

title: spanakopita
directions: Prepare fresh spinach; sprinkle with salt.
Tear into small pieces; rinse thoroughly.
Drain.
Beat the eggs.
Crumble Feta cheese and mix.
Add this to spinach.
Chop onion; saute in olive oil.
Add to spinach mixture.
Season with pepper and oregano.

title: tuna dill sandwich
directions: Stir dressing, dill and pepper.
Add tuna, onion and carrot; mix well.
For each sandwich, top one muffin half with lettuce, cheese and tuna mixture.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chops 1/2 at a time with onion 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until chops are fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time: 3 minutes; cook time:
30 minutes.

title: easy chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain; arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bacon snacks
directions: Sprinkle cheese on crackers.
Wrap in bacon (1/3 slice each). Bake at 200° for 2 to 4 hours.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Mix in bowl the crackers, dill weed, oil and dressing.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn crackers every 5 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Place a slice of pineapple on crisp lettuce on a salad plate. Combine precooked shrimp, thinly sliced celery, green pepper strips and minced onion to taste.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Season well and heap on pineapple on salad plate.
Garnish with olives and deviled eggs.

title: chili
directions: Use food processor and finely chop the clove of garlic.
Brown garlic with ground beef.
Put tomatoes, onion and green pepper in blender; blend well.
Onions and green pepper will be larger pieces, so don't blend too much.
Add to meat in skillet.
Add tomato paste and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer and cook 1 hour.
Add kidney beans; heat through.
Serve with oyster crackers or crusty French bread.

title: dressing
directions: Saute chopped
celery and onion in oleo in iron skillet until tender.
Chop
boiled eggs and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, adding
chopped
eggs	last.
Bake
in
375° oven until brown on top.

title: easy punch
directions: Fill punch bowl with ice.
Mix juices in pitcher; add ginger ale to thin.
Mix well.
Pour over ice; add more ginger ale to fill; stir.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter; make a crust in the bottom of a long cake pan.
Mix powdered sugar and 3 eggs and beat with an electric mixer and pour over crust.
Add sliced bananas; top with Cool Whip, then sprinkle with cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: apple butter(crock-pot)
directions: Slow cook apples for 17 hours on low.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on high for 8 hours.

title: rhineland potato salad
directions: Cook bacon, onion and green pepper until bacon is crisp. Drain and add to remaining ingredients; toss lightly.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Thaw bread and break apart in 13 x 9-inch pan (small pieces). Combine and heat brown sugar, oleo, milk, cinnamon, vanilla pudding and chopped nuts or coconut.
Heat until blended.
Do not cook.
Pour over dough pieces and let rise to rim of pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one dish chicken bake
directions: Sift stuffing crumbs, seasoning packet, 1 1/2 cups hot water, and 1/4 cup margarine until just moistened; set aside.
Place chicken in 9x13 inch baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 375 degrees for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. 4 servings.
tags: Stove Top Stuffing mix for chicken

title: pecan tart christmas cookies
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter. Add flour. Refrigerate 1 hour. Divide into 2 dozen balls. Pat into muffin tins. Beat egg, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and nuts. Drop into filled muffin tins, filling 1/2 to 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Enjoy!

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the buttermilk to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over lukewarm milk and stir until dissolved.
Allow to stand a few minutes and then add remaining buttermilk.
Blend well.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal, cool 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; mix.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add cooled oatmeal.
Add nuts, coconut and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured oblong baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and cool.
Mix chopped vegetables and olives with kraut and sprouts in a large Pyrex bowl.
Pour vinegar and sugar over it and mix well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hockey puck potatoes
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and place mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Crumble on top cornflakes mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add vegetables and mix well. Combine milk, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add these ingredients to macaroni mixture.
Mix thoroughly and chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cook chicken. Combine chicken and soy sauce. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Let sit for 15 minutes. Cook rice in hot oil. Reduce heat. Add chicken and broth. Simmer, covered, 20 to 25 minutes. Stir in onions, green peppers and celery. Cook, uncovered. Push rice to side. Add eggs and cook until almost set. Blend into rice. Stir in lettuce or red cabbage.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: mom's coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 325° until set.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes. Start counting when mixture has reached a full rolling boil. Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter. Mix well until blended. Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: salmon and asparagus chantilly
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Remove skin and bone.
Add enough milk to salmon juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk and salmon juice.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add onion, mustard, salt, pepper, mayonnaise, and parsley flakes.
Combine sauce, salmon, eggs and asparagus spears.
Place in shallow 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in buttered 9 x 13 casserole. Mix crushed corn flakes with 1/4 c. melted margarine and sprinkle over top.

title: danish cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Then add vanilla, nuts and dates.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 300°.
When brown, remove from stove and while still hot, cover with the icing.

title: orange refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add the egg and the orange rind and juice or extract.
Beat vigorously.
Then add the dry ingredients, sifted together.
Shape into two rolls and cover with wax paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice one-fourth-inch thick. Bake in a hot oven, 400°, for about ten minutes.
Makes about thirty cookies.
(These are good decorated with icing, fruit or nuts.)

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Bring 2 cups sugar and water to a boil. Take off heat after comes to boil. Cut up peaches. Set aside.

title: rice pudding(arrozo doce #2)
directions: In a 1 to 1 1/2-quart saucepan bring the milk, vanilla bean, cinnamon stick, pieces of lemon peel and 1/8 teaspoon of salt to a boil over moderate heat.
Cover the pan tightly.
Remove from heat and let the seasonings steep for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge recipe 2
directions: Stir milk, butter and sugar until it boils; boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter over melted oleo.
Drop fruit over batter, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain the sweet potatoes and mash.
Add eggs, granulated sugar, flavoring and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Mix flour, brown sugar, margarine and nuts separately.
Spread over the top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed vienna bread
directions: Stuff mushrooms, cheese and olives in cracks of bread.
Place on large piece of foil.
Microwave butter, green pepper, onions, salt, lemon juice and mustard 2 minutes.
Pour over bread.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crunchy waldorf salad
directions: Gently combine all ingredients.
Chill until serving time. Serve on lettuce.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add eggs, flour and salt.
Mix well, then add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan (about 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch - an open roasting pan does well).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cover top, while still hot, with marshmallow cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat with an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate cake with creamy icing
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk.
Mix about 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°. Good with ham in place of vegetable. Also good as dessert; warm or cold.

title: mini taco cups
directions: Mix together the tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Cook and drain ground beef, then add taco mix.
Cut into quarters 1 package dinner rolls.
Press pieces into mini muffin pans (greased). Form a cup and fill with meat mixture. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Use a teaspoon to get out of pan.

title: teacher's perk coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Place the frozen dinner rolls in Bundt pan (extra large size).
If you don't have this pan, divide between 2 regular size Bundt pans, or experiment with a sheet pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Mix together the brown sugar and vanilla pudding.
Sprinkle the pudding mixture on top of the pecans.
Pour the melted margarine over the rolls. Spray plastic wrap with nonstick cooking spray; cover Bundt pan(s).
Leave on counter overnight.
In morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter bottom of pan.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Do not mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in water until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter, soup, and crackers.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Velveeta slices.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: potato zucchini casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a greased casserole.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: 106 year old pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and put in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: eclair
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with some of the crackers. Pour cold milk into bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat at low speed on mixer until well blended (1 to 2 minutes). Let stand for 5 minutes. Then blend in Cool Whip. Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers. Add another layer of crackers. Top with remaining pudding mixture. Top with remaining crackers. Spread pie filling or frosting over top. (Frosting works better if warmed just a few seconds in microwave to make more spreadable.) Chill 3 hours or overnight.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, sherry, sugar, ginger, 5 spice powder and cornstarch together. Marinate the wings for 15 minutes.
Deep fry in 375° peanut oil until the wings are golden brown and tender.

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling water 5 minutes and drain. Combine soup, cheese, sour cream and carrots; fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and oleo.
Put 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom of pan.
Place squash mixture on stuffing.
Cover top of squash mixture with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Spread over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with green beans.
Top with mashed potatoes. Drizzle melted butter over potatoes.
Bake at 325° until browned, approximately 20 minutes.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: This makes a large bowl.
Don't mix these until the last thing and then add cream.

title: finger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and powdered sugar; blend in flour.
Press evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot baked layer.
Return to oven to bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool about 15 minutes in pan before cutting into bars.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease 8 muffin cups or line with paper bake cups. Set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar and oil. Add vanilla.
Beat until lemon color, add zucchini and stir.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir well. Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.
Take out and thump bottom of pans to test to see if done.
Set for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to cool completely.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: To slightly beaten egg yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Cook until thick in double boiler.
Pour cold water into bowl and sprinkle gelatine on top of water.
Add to hot pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly; cool.
When it begins to thicken, add remaining sugar and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into large baked pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator or cold place.
Pie may be garnished with whipped cream just before serving.
This is delicious in a gingersnap crust.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Place dough in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on floured board, about 1/8-inch thick. Cut in 2-inch squares. Fill with favorite filling.
Roll into crescents. Bake at 400° until light brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart souffle dish with butter and sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Stir flour and melted butter together.
Let foam and cook 2 minutes without browning. Remove from heat, pour in hot milk and beat.
Return to heat and boil, stirring for 1 minute.
Sauce will be very thick.
Remove from heat and beat the egg yolks into the hot mixture, one at a time.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg to taste.

title: refrigerator breakfast sweet rolls(yields 36 rolls)
directions: Scald milk and set aside to cool to lukewarm.
Put 1 teaspoon of sugar and yeast in the 1/4 cup water.
Sift flour into large bowl and add salt, lemon rind and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut the 1 cup butter into flour mix as for pie crust with pastry blender.
Add beaten eggs and yeast to cooled milk.
Combine lightly with flour-butter mix.
Stir until well mixed but don't beat.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold nuts in batter, then egg whites. Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices. Combine soup with milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix or croutons over top and drizzle with margarine. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar and flour. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat 6 to 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Stir 1 cup hot mixture into egg yolks; immediately return to saucepan and hot mixture.
Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup coconut, margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: surprise salad
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan until it comes to a boil; stir in gelatins until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip to mixture.
Put in glass dish.
Refrigerate.

title: banana split freeze
directions: Slice bananas and place on crust.
Layer ice cream on top. Sprinkle with nuts and freeze. Combine chips, oleo, powdered sugar and milk.
Cook and stir until thick. Add vanilla and cool.
Pour cooled sauce on ice cream and freeze.
Top with Dream Whip.
(Can fold in pineapple or strawberries.)
Freeze. Serves 15 to 18. Will keep 1 month in freezer.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Bake chicken, garlic and onion at 350° for 1 hour, covered. Cool and chop chicken, reserving juice.

Add tomato, black olives, green pepper and cheeses to cooled chicken, onion and garlic. Wrap a handful of the chicken-vegetable-cheese mixture into each tortilla and place on a 10 x 15-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Clean and cut chicken into serving pieces.
Brown in hot oil. Add vegetables and brown lightly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done.
If liquid evaporates, add a little water.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in pan.
Cut up stick of butter and place over peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix 2 cups sugar, flour and milk.
Pour batter over peaches and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: drew's p.b.j.
directions: Spread peanut butter over 1/2 of bread and jelly over the other half.
Fold together and eat.
You will love it as much as he does.

title: dilly ham balls
directions: In a bowl, combine ham, bread crumbs, onions, 1 tbsp fresh dill (1 tsp dried dill), milk, egg, mustard and 1/4 tsp pepper; mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
In a large skillet, heat 1 tbsp butter and 1 tbsp oil.
Brown ham balls, add remaining butter and oil as needed.
Remove ham balls to a serving dish, cover and keep warm.
Pour ham drippings into a sauce pan, blend in flour. Gradually add water and stir until smooth.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add sour cream and remaining dill and pepper, heat through, but do not boil.
Pour over the ham balls.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: venison roast
directions: Marinate venison in strong vinegar-water solution for about 2 hours.
Remove and rinse well.
Dry meat off.
Rub salt and red pepper into meat.

title: stuffed date drops
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light. Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients and mix alternating with sour cream. Stuff each date with nut quarter and add. Stir only to mix in dates.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet, 1 date to each cookie. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Top with Golden Frosting.

title: nettie's coleslaw
directions: Cut up cabbage, onion and pepper in a large bowl.
Bring all other ingredients to a boil and pour over the cabbage mixture. Let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Cut
chicken
into
1-inch
chunks.
In large saucepot, heat oil
over
medium-high heat.
Add chicken and sausage, a few pieces
at	a
time, and cook until browned on all sides, removing to plate as they brown.

title: shrimp stuffed mirlitons
directions: Simmer mirlitons in salted water until tender; cut in halves. Remove seeds and spoon out pulp.
Mix pulp and bread crumbs. Saute onions, garlic and shrimp in butter over medium heat about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently; cool.
Add egg, parsley and thyme.
Fill shells; sprinkle the top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Mix onion, tomatoes and corn.
Add mayonnaise to coat.

title: caramel filled chocolate cookies
directions: Beat together butter or margarine, sugars and vanilla until combined.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add to butter mixture and beat on low speed until just combined.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Cover and chill dough 1 hour.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix and pour melted margarine over top.
Shape into little balls.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Yields 48.

title: royal coconut cookies
directions: Sift flour, powder, soda and salt.
Add sugars, egg and flavoring.
Beat until smooth. Fold in oats and coconut.
Shape into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: Chop Potatoes. Put everything in a pot. Cook until the potatoes are done.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Place defrosted lemon juice and all ingredients in large container.
Add enough water to make 4 gallons.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with maraschino cherries frozen in ice cubes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Store in refrigerator in covered jar. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugar, butter, vanilla and milk until smooth.
If necessary, add more milk until frosting spreads smooth.
If desired, add a few drops of food coloring.
Can frost a two layer cake.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion together until tender.
Break corn bread and toast up in a large bowl.
Add celery and onion mixture and next 4 ingredients.
After mixing, put into baking dish or pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done to your likeness.

title: andrew's devil's food cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Dough will be very sticky. Using 2 spoons, dip a tablespoon amount out and roll in a bowl of powdered sugar to coat. Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes. Serve with a glass of cold moo juice!

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles with a little butter.
Drain.
Pour into casserole dish and mix soup and tuna with it.
Add bread crumbs sprinkled with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix sugar and eggs. Combine flour, meal, baking powder and salt. Add to the egg mixture; stir in melted butter and milk. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 baking pan for 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tortillas. Spread on tortillas and roll into log. Slice to desired size. Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: michigan lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Beat egg and mix with cottage cheese, parsley and garlic.
Brown beef and sausage (drain) and add Prego and tomato paste.
Simmer (if too thick, add a little water).
Coat 9 x 13-inch pan with a little oil.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, then egg and cheese mixture, then noodles.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Bake at 375° covered for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: old fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Pour beaten egg into the flour mixture and knead about 20 seconds. Brush with melted butter, pat out the remaining half of the dough over top.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Turn out on cooking rack.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and peppers, also mushroom if you prefer.
Cook sliced potatoes until tender.
Put a layer of ground beef mixture and then add potatoes and more soup.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes in a 375° oven.
Before you cook it, add a little milk on top.
It helps it to stay moist.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Boil rhubarb, sugar and pineapple for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Place in hot jars; cover with paraffin.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into
an
x 4 x 1 1/2 inch loaf.
Place in a lightly greased shallow pan.
Brush with 57 sauce, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow to set 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spareribs or chicken and potatoes
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot and cook for 2 hours or until tender.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Cook rice; mix with soup, corn, ro-tel. Put in casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 350°F. until cheese browns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 2 slices of cubed bread in the bottom of a casserole. Mix chicken, vegetables and mayonnaise.
Spoon over bread.
Add the other 4 slices of cubed bread over this.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over top of bread.
Cover and chill at least one hour or overnight.
Spoon mushroom soup over the top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
During last 10 minutes of baking, sprinkle cheese on top.

title: mom's french dressing
directions: Add ingredients to blender and blend for 1 minute.
Pour into bottle and refrigerate.

title: strawberry rhubarb soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat fruit and juice to boiling. Simmer about 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Add sugar; cool.
In covered blender at low speed, blend soup half at a time.
Pour into a bowl; add orange sections.
Refrigerate covered.
Serve in a chilled bowl; garnish with strawberry slices.

title: tea cakes
directions: Melt margarine, then add sugar and beat well.
Add 1 egg at a time beating after each one.
Then add vanilla flavoring and self-rising flour and beat.
Bake at 300° until edges are brown.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over the mixture. Put into refrigerator.
(This will keep indefinitely.)

title: italian cookies
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and sugar, making sure the baking powder is thoroughly blended in. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture and add oil, eggs, vanilla and anise.
Mix well and shape into a bow knot or twist on floured board.
Bake at 350° until light brown (about 10 minutes). Brush with powdered sugar glaze and sprinkle with nonpareils.

title: chicken a la king over biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients (except biscuits) in 1-quart casserole. Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) until hot and bubbly, 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir.
Serve over biscuits.
(I use Bisquick biscuits.)

title: sausage-cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Mix well eggs, half and half milk, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut crusts off bread and cube.
Place in the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Pour egg mixture over bread and sausage.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.

Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans and bananas. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken, cool, remove from bone and cut in big chunks. Mix crackers with melted margarine and poppy seed.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Cover bottom of pan with 1/2 of cracker mixture. Place chicken next and spread soup mixture over chicken.
Top with remaining cracker mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be frozen. Serves 6.

title: cabbage cheddar chowder
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, celery, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven until vegetables are tender; drain.
Stir in cabbage and water.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until cabbage is done (about 10 minutes).
Stir in milk, cheese, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Garnish with pimentos. Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Good with garlic crackers.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: In a serving bowl mix all the above ingredients.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: noodle burger bake
directions: Combine and brown meat and onions until tender.
Add all ingredients except bread crumbs and melted oleo and pour into oblong baking dish or casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and oleo. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: boursin
directions: Bring cream cheese and butter (or margarine) to room temperature.
Add herbs and spices; whip until light.
Pack into container; chill in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: super duper chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate down and mix with oil.
Add sugar and vanilla. Add eggs singly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add chocolate mixture and nuts to dry ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: all you can eat vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, add bouillon cubes, cabbage, celery, onions and carrots with water.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes, green beans and chicken broth.
Simmer an additional 30 minutes.

title: easy irish soda bread
directions: Mix biscuit mix, raisins, caraway seed and sugar.
Beat eggs and milk and add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir to form a sticky dough.
Knead on a lightly floured board a few times to form a smooth ball.
Cut dough into 2 pieces.
Shape pieces of dough into 2 smooth balls. Place balls on greased cookie sheets. With a sharp knife, cut a cross 1/2 inch deep in center of each ball.
Bake in preheated oven (400°) for 25 to 30 minutes until brown and center feels firm.
Cool thoroughly on rack before cutting.
Bread can be frozen in foil and thawed in wrapping 2 hours.

title: okra goulash
directions: Fry okra.
When the okra is almost done, add onion and a hot pepper.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Cook until done.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Toss with chicken and celery.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stir in grapes and pecans. Serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients, except milk, until crumbly.
Stir in milk until dough leaves side of bowl.
Put dough on lightly floured surface.
Knead ten times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into biscuits.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamed chicken in biscuit bowls
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Add onion, celery and mushrooms. Saut 2 to 3 minutes until tender. Whisk in chicken soup and milk and cook over medium-low heat 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add cheese, stirring constantly, until melted. Stir in chicken, peas, carrots, pimiento, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes. Spoon into Biscuit Bowls.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, vanilla and sugar; beat.
Add butter or margarine.
Add everything except flour.
Beat again.
Slowly add flour, beating continuously and scraping side of bowl.
If batter is too thick, add milk.
If too thin, add more flour.
Serves 2 hungry people.

title: vegetarian collard greens
directions: Cut greens and onions. Heat 1 cup water and a good amount of garlic olive oil with fresh garlic. Add cut greens and onions. Add water as it steams out. Cook for about 1 hour (until moist). Add seasonings for flavor.

title: cream of squash soup
directions: Slice squash; peel, quarter and slice onion.
Slice garlic cloves.
Cook with water 2 bouillon cubes and butter until tender. Mash with potato masher.
Mix cornstarch with 1 cup of the skim milk.
Add to mixture.
Stir until it starts to thicken then add rest of milk.
Tear or cut cheese into hunks and add.
Turn off heat and cover for 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.
More milk may be added.

title: apple valley cake(sauce makes the difference)
directions: Beat together oil and sugar; beat 3 minutes, then add flour (2 cups) and soda.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and salt.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: husbands delight
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: double batch corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Excellent side dish!

title: blueberry nectar pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put into your favorite pie crust. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon butter over filling.
Put on a top crust. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy meatloaf
directions: Mix egg, milk, cheese, oatmeal, onion and salt together.
Add hamburger.
Using ice cream scoop, place in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: monster cookies
directions: In large dishpan, mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli (or zucchini) casserole
directions: In boiling, salted water, add cut up broccoli and chopped onion.
Cook until tender.
Drain and cool.
Combine carrots, soup and sour cream and mix.
Set aside.
Melt margarine and add stuffing mix.
Toss to coat.
Put 1/2 of this in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine broccoli with soup mixture and put in casserole on top of stuffing mix.
Top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and drain cauliflower and broccoli.
Cut broccoli flowerets and cauliflower into small pieces.
Add sliced mushrooms.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls on a cookie sheet, pressing edges together to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour over cabbage.
