title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Add margarine.
Cool. Beat 2 eggs and add to chocolate chips mixture.
Add mini marshmallows, stir quickly.
Form into 3 rolls by globbing on tinfoil.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Reroll in new tinfoil and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
In 2-quart casserole, combine soup, sour cream and salt.
Stir in rice, chicken and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions and bake an additional 5 to 8 minutes or until onions are deep golden brown.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: do not stir cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Make batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter into melted margarine in casserole dish.
Add fruit and juice. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jackie's muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease muffin pan or baking loaf pan. Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 25 minutes. Makes 6 medium muffins.

title: pronto pups
directions: Heat deep-fry with oil to 375°.
Blend egg and milk; stir in dry ingredients.
Dip wieners in batter.
Fry until brown 2 or 3 minutes on each side.
To reheat, place in 400° oven about 5 minutes.

title: old fashioned cream puffs
directions: Heat water, butter, sugar and salt to a rolling boil in saucepan.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously with a wooden spoon until thick and smooth (about 1 minute) staying away from the sides.
Remove from heat and add eggs one at a time beating well after each egg.
Use a wooden spoon or electric mixer until paste is shiny and smooth.
Drop tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Fill each cream puff with instant pudding, vanilla or chocolate.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Mix beef, salt and pepper; form into 8 patties.
Brown in skillet (use shortening if needed); pour off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over burgers.
Simmer 20 minutes or until done.
Stir now and then.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: hungarian veal and peppers
directions: Spray Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Saute over medium-high heat the onions and peppers for 5 minutes; set aside.
Dredge veal in flour; saute for 5 minutes.
Add pepper mixture and mushrooms to veal and the next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour, or until veal is tender, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and cook an additional 10 minutes. Serve over noodles.
Equally good made with boneless and skinless chicken breasts.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage, onion, peppers and carrots.
Let stand for 1 1/2 hours.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for several days. Serves 25.

title: double almond cookies
directions: Prepare and chill dough for Basic Sliced Cookies as directed.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In skillet, brown meatballs, turning occasionally; drain.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over meatballs; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 4 dozen meatballs.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add hot water and knead until smooth. Tear off small amounts and roll into ball.
Roll out flat with rolling pin.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Turn.
Be careful not to overcook.

title: pastitso
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain. Add water and tomato paste. Cook macaroni; drain. Add margarine and cheese. Cook milk, 1/2 cup margarine, cornstarch and water until thick; cool. Beat eggs until yellow. Add seasonings and cheese. In 2-quart casserole, layer the meat, macaroni and sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and then cream them.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in ungreased casserole dish at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat softened oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and cocoa; beat well.
Add pecans. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
While still hot, cover with marshmallows or marshmallow cream.
Place in oven that has been turned off until marshmallows melt.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.
Stir pudding mix into milk in large saucepan.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust. Place plastic wrap on surface of filling.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Garnish as desired.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma's pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 c. hot pear juice. Beat in cream cheese with mixture while juice is hot. Let jell 10 minutes. Stir in mashed pears and cool whip. Top with crushed pecans. Refrigerate.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Combine in large bowl

title: chocolate beer cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar slowly and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating until well blended.
Add chocolate and beat until smooth.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt 3 times.
Add alternately with beer, a little at a time.
Add the beaten egg whites. Bake in oblong pan at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: almond butter
directions: Melt butter in a heavy pan.
Heat carefully to golden brown. Add almonds and lemon juice.
Serve with broccoli, cauliflower and asparagus.

title: chokecherry marinade
directions: Pound steak.
Put in wide-mouth jar or crock.
Pour marinade over meat.
Let stand overnight in cool place.
Also for roast. Best marinade for dip.

title: luscious lemon drops
directions: In large bowl, combine dry cake mix, whipped topping, egg, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Stir to mix well, but do not overmix.

title: hot dogs and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: smaker doodles cookies
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to Crisco, eggs and sugar mixture.
Chill dough. Roll ball about size of walnut.
Roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
The cookies will puff up and then flatten out.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place cubed steak in skillet.
Simmer in suet until fairly tender.
Add garlic clove for 1/2 hour; remove.
Add onion and cook until thin.
Add bouillon broth as well, then add the tomatoes and pepper.
Continue simmering until tomatoes and peppers are thin and meat is tender.
Add cornstarch to desired thickness.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Serve over cooked rice or Chinese noodles.

title: oyster soup
directions: Cook oysters, onion and celery until tender.
Make paste of cornstarch and water; put into oyster mixture and pour milk in.

title: chili pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in 3-quart casserole so that "tails" are in center.
Place onion and pepper slices on top of chops.
Pour chili sauce on top.
Microwave on Medium for 30 to 35 minutes. Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Clean strawberries and divide between 2 baked pie shells. Heat mixture except jello until clear and thick.
Remove from heat; add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over strawberries in baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip after jelled.

title: no bake cheesecake(low-fat)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, vanilla and Cool Whip until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Garnish with pie cherries. Chill until set, at least 4 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Grate cheese.
Brown ground beef.
Cook noodles.
Layer ground beef, noodles, cheese and sauce at least twice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Place sauce in bottom of casserole dish, on top of ground beef, on top of noodles and on top of cheese.)

title: chili
directions: Mix together and cook slow for 1 hour.

title: ice cream sundae dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Melt butter.
Stir cookies into butter and press into dish; freeze. Spread vanilla ice cream on top of cookies; freeze.
Top with the following fudge sauce which has been previously made and cooled. Cook unsweetened baking chocolate, sugar and milk to boiling until thick.
When cool, add vanilla and spread on ice cream; freeze. Spread prepared whipped topping, a sprinkle of nuts and position a cherry for each serving, in that order, on top of fudge sauce. Freeze.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ranch, bacon and cheddar dip
directions: Mix dip mix and sour cream. Then add bacon bits and cheese. Mix well and serve with chips.

title: easy cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Unroll 1 package crescent rolls in to 1 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat out.
Mix filling and spread over.
Unroll other package of crescent rolls and put over top.
"Paint" the egg white over the top and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon (a generous amount). Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet pickle strips
directions: Wash cucumbers. Cut in strips. Pour boiling water over them. Let stand 4 to 5 hours. Drain and pack solidly in jars. Boil solution 5 minutes. Pour boiling hot over pickles in jars. Cook in hot water bath for 5 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: veggie squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayo, and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing until smooth.
Fold in gradually each of the chopped vegetables (except tomatoes and Cheddar cheese).
Spread mixture over crescent rolls.
Chill.
Top with tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Cut into squares and serve.
(It is best to refrigerate overnight before serving.)

title: sissy's five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Alternately add flour and baking powder with milk.
Add extracts last.
Bake in greased, 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: poi cocktail
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a big glass and serve like a milk shake.

title: tin plate special
directions: Wash beans.
Cover with cold water and let soak overnight. Bring beans to a boil and cook 1 hour.
Drain, discarding water. Brown roast in hot fat in a large Dutch oven or roaster.
Add pepper and onions and cook until tender.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until beans are tender and meat is done.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and saute small pieces of chipped beef.
Add flour and mix well, then add onion and white pepper. Stir in milk as mixture thickens.
Add sour cream.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Pepper meat and then place in roasting bag, following bag directions.
Add the 2 soups over meat and seal bag.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.
Serve with potatoes.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together sweet potato and banana.
Add milk, blending well.
Add brown sugar, egg yolks and salt; mixing thoroughly.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix butter with mixer until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugars.
Combine
flour, baking soda and cocoa, beginning and ending with flour mixture.	Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and
minutes
or
until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
in
pan
on	a wire 10 to 15 minutes. Remove
from pan
and cool completely on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.	Yields 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: autumn soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir meat until brown; drain off excess fat.
Cook and stir onion with meat until onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes; heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease off.
Mix tomatoes, salt, pepper, chili powder, sugar, water and rice in bowl.
Mix good. Add to meat and onion.
Cook until rice is tender.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix fruit and marshmallows with cream cheese and add whipping cream or Dream Whip.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.

title: chocolate malt ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour in freezer.
Add regular milk to fill line.
Stir and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: 1-2-3-4 basic cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry items, one cup at a time.
Add vanilla extract.
Bake at 350° in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Complete with your favorite topping.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix vegetables, relish and bacon together.
Mix mayonnaise and 1/4 cup pickle juice.
Place 1/2 of crumbled bread in bowl.
Next, layer 1/2 of the mixed vegetables and top with 1/2 of the mayonnaise topping.
Repeat with bread, vegetables and mayonnaise topping.
Chill overnight.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Crush graham crackers; mix in bowl with melted butter.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Follow directions on pudding box.
When pudding is cooked, add cream cheese; mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook
all
ingredients	until
tender.	Then add 2 cups mashed potatoes to make soup thicken.

title: ham balls
directions: Grind ham, pork and beef. Add graham cracker crumbs, egg and milk. Mix and shape into balls. Top with sauce: tomato soup, vinegar, brown sugar and dry mustard. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato and egg
directions: Peel, wash and dry potatoes to fill skillet, slightly layering.
Cook sliced potatoes on a medium heat until brown and crispy.
Beat the eggs.
Add seasonings to taste.
Pour eggs over potatoes in skillet; cook until set.
Turn the potatoes over to brown on the other side.
Turn out of skillet; cut into serving pieces.

title: grits casserole
directions: Add butter and cheese to grits; stir until blended.
Add eggs and milk.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 40 minutes.

title: trucker's beans
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add hot pepper seeds, if desired.
Mix meat mixture with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 300° to 350° oven until done, about 2 hours.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, oats, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Mix well and pack into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake loaf at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut a
broiler into small pieces.
In a deep frying pan with a cover,
heat
3 tablespoons olive oil; add chicken and brown until
golden
on
all
sides.
(If desired, skin can be removed.) Add chopped onion, parsley, basil, salt and pepper. Brown together with chicken until onion is golden.
Pour over all 1/2 cup
wine
(white
or red).
Cover and let simmer for about a minute;
add
tomatoes
that have been crushed with a fork.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: scotch bread cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add sifted flour.
Roll very thin.
Cut and bake at 325° about 20 minutes.

title: cooked chicken salad
directions: Cook egg noodles in
chicken broth (as many cups cooked egg noodles as
chicken).
Mix
ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May top with crushed potato chips.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix equal amounts of apple juice and ginger ale to freeze a mold, to put in punch bowl.
Then add equal amounts of chilled apple juice and ginger ale to punch bowl.

title: beef tips with mushrooms and onions
directions: Melt margarine in a large saute pan.
Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic. Remove from pan with broth remaining.
Add sirloin and brown over medium heat. Remove meat to dish with mushrooms and onions.

Add remaining ingredients to broth in pan, making sure to make a paste with cornstarch first to avoid having lumps in gravy. Stir this constantly until mixture thickens. Add back the beef, mushrooms and onions and mix together with gravy. Pour this into a large casserole dish.
At this point the dish can be refrigerated for cooking the next day. Bake, covered, in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
This is delicious served with rice and green beans. Also a good dish to fix on Saturday and cook on Sunday morning for a perfect Sunday lunch.
Enjoy!

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill.
tags: Thank You lite cherry pie filling

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in the cup of water about 2 hours.
Add this and other ingredients to cake mix and mix well.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake about 35 minutes at 325°.
Turn pan upside down to cool.
Glaze with your favorite glaze.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put chuck roast into crock-pot.
Add all ingredients to this. Add enough water to cover just over the ingredients.
Cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.
May be best to add your cut up potatoes last so it won't be mushy.
You can add the last hour.

title: choco-peanut squares
directions: Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil (foil should be over edges of pan).
In medium pan, combine sugar and syrup.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Remove from heat; add cereal, stirring until combined.
Press cereal in pan. Microwave chocolate chips for 1 minute (all will not be melted). Spread on cereal.
Wait 5 minutes, then spread evenly.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Lift cereal out.
Peel off foil and cut.

title: zucchini and corn bake
directions: Cook zucchini in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Mix together onion, zucchini, corn, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased baking dish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and spoon dressing over salad several hours before serving or for crispier salad, just before serving.

title: boysenberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, shortening and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, water, vinegar and walnuts.
Mix well.
Press into 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Saute celery and bell pepper in 1/2 stick of butter.
Boil egg noodles in chicken broth to cook.
Add chicken, mushroom soup, celery mixture and egg noodles and simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with creamed mixture.

title: buffalo shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Dip shrimp in sauce.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sour cream, soup, cheeses and onion into large bowl.
Stir until mixed.
Break apart any large clumps of hash browns while in package, then combine and stir into other ingredients.
Spray 9 x 13-inch glass pan with a nonstick oil pan coating.
Pour into pan and add diced margarine on top. Bake for 1 hour.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain, and retain grease.
Saute onions and celery in 2 Tbsp of grease until tender.
Mix bread cubes, browned sausage, onions, celery, all spices and orange juice.
Stir in the remaining grease.
Add chicken broth to moisten (1 to 2 small cans).
Place in a baking dish.
Pour the remaining butter over the dressing.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.

title: abby's sprinkle toast
directions: Place bread on cookie sheet.
Spread margarine over bread, then add sprinkles or cinnamon sugar.
Broil until toasted.

title: summer float
directions: In 10 ounce glass, put 3 or 4 scoops of vanilla frozen yogurt. Pour Kern's peach juice to fill glass.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into a ball.
Roll in nuts (optional).
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes 1 large cheese ball.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and onion in saucepan with small amount of water.
Cook until tender. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with some crumbled crackers and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 35 minutes until top is brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Combine water, sugar and cherries.
Boil gently 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add pineapple (do not drain), nuts and cola.
Place into mold and chill.
(I think it's better the second day.)

title: twinkie dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, lay Twinkies, side by side (cream side up) in 2 rows. Spread with pineapple. Cover with bananas. Prepare pudding according to package directions.
When thickened, spread over bananas. Refrigerate. Before serving, top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: martha's lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed; bake in 3 layers.
Cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherries, pineapple and nuts in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
In bowl, cut oleo with 2 knives into dry cake mix and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cucumber-dill pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Chill until serving time.

title: zesty barbecued ribs
directions: In small bowl, stir together barbecue sauce, horseradish, prepared mustard and Worcestershire sauce until well blended. Place spareribs in large saucepan; add water.
Cover; bring to boil over high heat and boil gently 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Brush ribs with sauce.
Grill, brushing with sauce and turning frequently, 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add cream and cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
Boil pasta; drain.
Put sauce over pasta; add 3/4 of the ham and cheese.
Add black pepper.
Toss and add rest of ham and cheese.
As a side dish, omit ham.

title: italian pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package, also add bouillon cubes to water while cooking.
Saute garlic in small skillet in 1 tablespoon olive oil for about 3 minutes.
Cook broccoli in microwave for 4 minutes.
Cook corn in microwave for 4 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cabinet pudding
directions: Dissolve 2 tablespoons Knox plain gelatine in 3/4 cup cold water; stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Add dissolved gelatine to custard.
Set custard mixture aside to cool.
When custard mixture is cool, pour into macaroon mixture.
Mix well; cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serve in dessert dishes and top with whipped cream.
This dessert was Mother's favorite to serve at parties and special dinners.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix well!
Bake at 300° for 2 hours in greased and floured tube pan.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place foil on countertop for cooling cookies. Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat on medium speed with electric mixer until well blended. Beat egg into mixture. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Mix into creamed mixture just until blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, longer for crisp cookies.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix, chill and serve.
Very good on crackers.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Soften cream
cheese;
beat
in mayo and add Cool Whip. Fold in	remaining
ingredients.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch cake pan; freeze and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Combine all other ingredients and simmer on low heat.

title: easy microwave chicken
directions: Prepare chicken breasts and place in microwave dish. Bake on High for about 20 minutes (until chicken is done).
Pour out juice.
Pour Ragu over chicken.
Put sliced cheese over sauce. Put back into microwave and heat sauce and melt cheese, 2 to 5 minutes. Serve over noodles or as a main dish. Quick and delicious.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.
Brush with melted butter and parsley while hot.

title: delmarva crab and corn chowder
directions: *Four cups defatted chicken broth may be used instead of clam juice and water.

title: buttermilk loaf cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in vanilla, lemon juice and rind.

Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Turn batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove and continue cooling on racks.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, then shortening and flavorings.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 325° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: duchess bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon; drain and remove.
Slice into fat the onions in rings.
When brown, add brown sugar, vinegar, garlic powder and salt.
Cook 20 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Pour sauce over this mixture:
butter beans, green beans, limas and kidney beans.
Add baked beans.
Stir and break bacon into mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana creme delight
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Add pudding and slowly beat in milk.
Fold in 4 ounces Cool Whip; reserve rest for top.
Line a 9-inch pan with wafers.
Slice bananas on top of wafers.
Top with pudding mixture.
Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Cook macaroni until done and drain. Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Drain and add spaghetti sauce.
Pour all ingredients into an oblong pan and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 325 degrees until cheese starts to brown.

title: cool pink salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill in refrigerator until very firm. May be served as a congealed salad or put in 2 graham cracker crusts and served as a pie.

title: a holland potato
directions: Wash potato.
Place onion on top of potato.
Wrap bacon around potato and onion.
Wrap all three in aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Rotate once while baking.

title: saucy barbecue franks
directions: Brown hot dogs with onions and bell peppers.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and whole milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute at rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats and stir well.
Drop by the teaspoon on wax paper or foil; let cool.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Will need a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Slice bananas into gelatin mixture.
Add frozen strawberries and undrained pineapple.
Pour half the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
In mixer bowl, beat cream with sour cream and sugar; spread over chilled layer.
Gently spoon remaining gelatin mixture on top.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into squares; serve on lettuce-lined salad plates. Garnish with additional pineapple.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter,
Crisco
and
sugar
in mixing bowl until fluffy.
Add
eggs,
1 at a time, beating after each addition. Sift flour and
measure.
Add salt and cocoa to flour and sift again.
Add
flour	mixture
alternately
with
fruit juice to creamed mixture and mix well.
Do not overmix.
Add flavor and mix well.
Pour into greased and
floured
10-inch
tube
pan. Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes.
Blend with remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell or into 2 small pie shells.
This is to be topped with applesauce topping.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions and garlic in oil; add mushrooms.
Sprinkle meat with 4 tablespoons flour and brown.
Add soup, water and seasonings.
Put in 300° oven for 1 hour.
Remove.
Add sour cream.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: quick hearty nacho dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in large skillet until meat is brown; drain.
Add beans, picante sauce and taco seasoning mix. Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until blended.
Spoon into 12 x 8 x 2 dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger, diced onion.
Drain off excess fat. Pour hamburg, bacon and onion in large casserole dish.
Combine beans, soup, brown sugar.
Mix with hamburg mixture.
Bake uncovered 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marvelous cookies(3 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet with margarine. Cream margarine, oil and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add whole wheat flour, salt, baking powder, wheat germ, rolled oats, raisins and nuts and mix well.
Add water if too dry.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Pour in a large saucepan and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: supreme salad
directions: First, chop the lettuce two or three times.
Put in a large bowl.
Next, add the sliced tomatoes.
Then add the carrots, cheese and the Bac*Os.
Finally select a salad dressing and spread the dressing.
Then serve.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Beat in thoroughly eggs, milk, vanilla and butter. Fold in pecans or walnuts. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: great guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Process until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: colorful candy popcorn balls
directions: Pour popcorn into a huge bowl.
Add peanuts and M&M's.
Mix together.
Put in margarine and marshmallows in a large microwaveable bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed (or you can use a saucepan and cook until marshmallows are puffed).
Mix margarine and marshmallow together.
Add gelatin to marshmallow mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over popcorn mixture.
Slightly grease hands well. Shape mixture into balls and place on waxed paper until completely cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine and cook until it forms firm ball in cold water, then add 2 cups raw peanuts.
Cook until light brown or honey colored. Add vanilla, small chunk butter, then add soda and stir quickly until thoroughly dissolved.
Pour onto Reynolds Wrap while still foaming.
Be sure not to overstir after adding soda.
Let cool thoroughly and break into pieces.

title: vanilla rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in a saucepan. Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.

title: *twists cookies 1(koulourakia)
directions: Cream the butter for 15 minutes. Add sugar gradually and beat an additional 15 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. Add baking powder, then add flour gradually, until it doesn't stick to your hands. Form dough into balls the size of a walnut. Roll dough with the palms of your hands to an 8-inch length.
Fold in half and give it a couple of twists.
Put on cookie sheet lined with tinfoil.
Brush with beaten egg (sesame seed optional).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake and cool. Crumble 1/2 of cake in punch bowl. Mix pudding with milk. Pour 1/2 of pudding over 1/2 of cake. add 1/2 of cool whip. Repeat layers and top with 2 large butterfinger candy bars that have been crushed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger together three times.
Beat eggs until thick, adding sugar gradually as you beat.
Whip in the pumpkin, then melted butter.
Beat in the dry ingredients and mix well. Fold in the nuts.
Pour into 2 buttered and floured pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: wild rice and sausage(yields 12 servings)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large skillet; cook over medium heat until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except almonds; mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 3-quart casserole and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, eggs and pineapple thoroughly.
Line an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Spread half the pineapple mixture over the vanilla wafers.
Add another layer of vanilla wafers.
Top with remaining pineapple mixture. Refrigerate.

title: granny carnala's chocolate pie
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thickens.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites for meringue.

title: chili con queso
directions: In a bowl, toss cheese lightly with cornstarch and garlic powder.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Brown beef.
Add onions and peppers to beef and cook until onion and pepper are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Toss with cooked pasta. Spoon into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Skin and wash chicken.
Salt and pepper.
Melt 1 stick margarine in roaster.
Crumble crackers in butter.
Roll chicken in buttered crumbs.
Place in roaster.
Make sure all chicken is covered.
Bake in covered dish for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon and save juice; mix with ingredients and add enough juice to spread.

title: white chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt grated white chocolate in 1/3 cup of the crisco oil on low heat and set aside. Put remainder of oil, eggs and cake mix in large bowl. Mix on low speed until well blended. Add melted chocolate and mix 1 minute. Mix water and pudding together and add to batter. Mix 2 minutes on medium speed. Add vanilla. Fold in chopped pecans and coconut, mix well. Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake at 350° preheated oven for 40 - 50 minutes or until done. Cool 15 minutes in pan before turning out.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread into small pieces and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon cooked sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
The cheese will rise to the top during baking.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Chop up into small pieces about 5 slices of bacon and one yellow onion.
Season with salt and pepper and fry over medium heat until bacon starts to just crisp and onion get soft.
Add 1/2 head of coarsely chopped cabbage.
Drizzle about 3 tablespoons of olive oil over the cabbage.
Season again with salt and pepper to taste. Continue stir frying over medium heat until cabbage is soft.
About 15 minutes.
You can also add some chopped apples to this to give it a sweet taste.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Cornbread tops this beef and bean casserole.

title: impossible turkey and stuffing pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4 inches). Mix turkey, peas, onions and cranberries in pie plate.
Separate stuffing into small pieces on turkey mixture.
Stir
remaining ingredients with fork until blended.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with hot turkey gravy, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: isaac's homemade powdered donut holes
directions: Cut each canned biscuit into four pieces and deep fry.
Put powdered sugar in a paper bag.
Put cooked pieces into bag of sugar and shake.
Voila! Donut holes!

title: malacados
directions: Sift flour.
Make well; add butter, sugar, salt, eggs and milk with yeast in it.
Mix well.
Cover with towel and put in warm place to rise (about 2 1/2 hours).
After it rises, pull in the sides and let rise again.
Fry in deep fat.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Soften crackers in 2 cups milk and hold aside.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mix and beat well.
Then add vanilla, coconut, pecans and baking powder and mix well.
Pour in greased baking pan.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour, using tube or layer cake pans.
Ice cake with mixture of 1 pound confectioners sugar, 1/2 pound butter and small drained can of crushed pineapple.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl of electric mixer, combine granulated and brown sugars, peanut butter, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at high speed until light and creamy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to egg mixture.
Stir to mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Spread dough (it will be quite stiff) evenly in greased cake pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until a rich golden brown.
Test with cake tester as you test any cake.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook all together on top of stove until pork is done.
Cool. Grind in meat grinder.

title: apricot kielbasa
directions: One day before party, slice kielbasa into bite-size pieces. Mix apricot preserves and nectar to make a pourable sauce.
Pour sauce over pieces and refrigerate 24 hours.
Prior to party, microwave or bake to heat kielbasa.
Arrange pieces on serving platter with toothpicks.
Provide hot mustard for dipping.
Serve warm.

title: jelly pie
directions: Put it in a bowl and mix them.
Freeze it for 50 minutes.

title: spicy apple pancakes with cider sauce
directions: Beat baking mix, cinnamon, egg and milk with rotary beater until smooth.
Stir in apple.
Grease griddle if necessary.
Pour batter by 1/4-cup measuring cupfuls onto hot griddle.
Bake until bubbles appear.
Turn; bake other side until golden brown.
Serve with warm Cider Sauce.
If you wish, top with dairy sour cream. Makes 18 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir apricots and nuts into batter.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 325° for glass pan or at 350° for metal pan.

title: pineapple marshmallow torte
directions: Melt marshmallows in saucepan with milk; cool thoroughly, stirring occasionally so it won't set.
When cooled, add the whipped cream and the drained pineapple.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 6 hours.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients, press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: italian deli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and chill well.

title: scallops
directions: Stir together the cheese, mayonnaise and wine; reserve.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter; add the scallops and cook, stirring, just until they are opaque, a minute or so.
With a slotted spoon, remove scallops to paper toweling to drain.
Add the remaining 2 tablespoons butter to the skillet with the onion; cook gently until slightly golden and add mushrooms.
Cook rapidly, stirring, so they do not release their liquid, a few minutes.
Turn off heat and stir in the reserved cheese mixture and scallops.
Bake in casserole until warmed through.
Serve over noodles.

title: green beans
directions: Cook on top of stove for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy irish potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large greased casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cook, covered, until the last 15 minutes. Stir occasionally. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: moussaka(a greek specialty)
directions: Brush both sides of eggplant slices with the oil; sprinkle with salt.
In large skillet, brown eggplant slices about 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain and set aside.
In same skillet, cook lamb or beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine, parsley, oregano, the 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon salt.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Gradually stir mixture into the 1 beaten egg.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery until crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside.
Cook ham, green pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet until golden.
Place ham mixture and cooked vegetables in deep greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and thyme.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add milk, cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper; melt cheese.
Pour sauce over mixture. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grilled chicken oriental
directions: In 1/2-cup metal measure or other small flameproof container, combine soy sauce with 2 tablespoons honey, oil, ginger and garlic. Cook, stirring frequently, until mixture is warm, about 1 minute. Transfer to self-sealing plastic bag or medium bowl (not aluminum). Add chicken and turn to coat with marinade. Seal bag or cover bowl and let stand 10 minutes to marinate.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Boil water and vinegar with onions, celery, carrot and spices. Allow to cool and pour over meat in pan.
Cover and set aside in cool place for 2 to 3 days.
Turn meat occasionally.
Remove from marinade; dry and rub with salt and pepper.
Soak raisins in cold water.
Heat fat in pan and sear meat on all sides.
Strain marinade and saute vegetables in same pan with meat.
Stir in tomato paste and add half of heated marinade.
Allow to simmer covered, for about 2 hours at medium heat.
Remove meat and keep warm.
Add remaining marinade to broth and stir.
Strain and quickly boil again with raisins and almonds, thicken with cornstarch.
Slice and serve with gravy.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Combine fruits, nuts and 1/2 cup flour to coat. Set aside. Cream butter. Add sugars and beat well. Add eggs and beat. Add soda and dry ingredients along with the milk. Stir in fruits and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. You can garnish the top of the cookie with fruit and nuts.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Add red pepper flakes, oregano and Velveeta.
Simmer on low until cheese melts.
Place a small amount on each piece of bread.
Place on a cookie sheet and broil until cheese bubbles.
Eat right away.

title: lemon-grape shimmer
directions: In a 2-quart non-metal pitcher, mix together all ingredients. Serve over ice in tall glasses.
Makes 7 (1-cup) servings.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, then add sugar gradually.
Beat until it's fluffy.
Add the beaten egg and the molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Gradually add milk, then add the raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp rolls
directions: Prepare marinade by combining sugar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, white wine and calamansi or lemon juice.
Shell shrimp, leaving tails.
Wrap shrimp with 2 to 3 strips each of carrot and spring onion in lumpia wrapper.
Roll.
Seal with cornstarch paste. Deep-fat fry.
Serve hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Stir
cucumbers,
onions, peppers and salt together and mix with
plenty
of crushed ice.
Place in vessel with weight on top and let stand 3 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix carrots, sugar, oil and beaten eggs together.
Gradually add remaining flour ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins with water for 15 minutes.
Add sugar, shortening and cold water.
Stir until sugar and shortening are dissolved. Cool.
Then add salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and flour. Mix well by hand.
Pour into a greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done when pressed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Fry 1 slice bacon or more until crispy. Pour off grease and mix with vinegar, sugar and egg.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix flour and sugar; sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with cheese, then crushed crackers.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion in small amount of margarine.
Add broth, rotel and soups.
Mix well.

title: eight layer jello salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, if possible, as this is a pretty salad.
Add 1 1/2 cups of boiling water to first package of Jell-O (black cherry or blackberry).
Pour into dish to set.

title: quick egg custard
directions: Grease pan with margarine; sprinkle with flour.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Pour into pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best of all fruit salad
directions: Peel and dice apples.
Add
juice of lemon to apples to keep from discoloring.
Boil
pineapple	juice
(reserved from can of pineapple).
Beat
eggs
lightly.
Mix sugar and flour. Add to eggs.
Pour boiling juice into this, stirring constantly, then place on stove
to	cook.
Cook until thickened.
Add butter. Remove from stove and cool.
When cooled add to fruit mixture.

title: brown sugar pumpkin pie(makes 8 servings)
directions: In medium bowl, cut margarine into flour until mixture is crumbly; stir in enough water until mixture forms a ball.
Set aside 1/4 of the dough; roll remaining dough into an 11-inch circle, about 1/8-inch thick.
Place in 9-inch pie plate; trim edge even with pie plate.
Roll out reserved dough and cut into 1-inch leaves; make vein marks in each leaf with back of knife. Attach leaves to edge of crust using 1 tablespoon egg product. Chill crust until ready to fill.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Saute sausage, onion and celery.
Drain off grease.
Add pork and beans and chili beans.
Add drained green beans, yellow beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Mix mustard, brown sugar and tomato soup.
Add to bean mixture and mix well.
Put in a large casserole or roaster.
Spread the tomato sauce on top of the bean mixture. Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Brown turkey in oil.
Combine rest of ingredients in sauce pan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over browned turkey and simmer 20 minutes more.

title: mary dell's fresh blueberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix lightly with washed, drained blueberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Place dots of butter all over fruit.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Place top crust over pie and slit.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with thick cream, whipped or plain.

title: zesty mozzarella chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk.
In another bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Dip each chicken breast in egg mixture and then in crumb mixture.
Melt butter in skillet; brown chicken on both sides until juices run clear.
Meanwhile, heat tomato sauce and basil until warm.
Sprinkle chicken with Mozzarella and serve with sauce.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: joe's oatmeal pecan cookies
directions: Combine white and brown sugars with Crisco and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and pecans and mix well.
(I mix all this with a pastry mixer or by hand.)
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie pan.
Bake at 375° for 11 or 12 minutes.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Cream butter; add sour cream.
Gradually add biscuit mix, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into lightly greased (or sprayed) mini-muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: morning glory bread
directions: Grease a 9-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, cream sugars and margarine until smooth and light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, bran, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add carrots, apples, raisins, nuts and coconut and toss to combine thoroughly.
Stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Spoon into loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: fly repellent spray
directions: Mix everything together.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Grate onions and eggs.
Mix eggs, onions and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix with squash and set aside. Crumble crackers, melt butter and mix.
Put one layer of squash mix and one layer of crackers, then bake 45 minutes or until brown.

title: quick and easy pasta
directions: Prepare Velveeta and shells according to directions on box. Brown hamburger; drain.
Pour Velveeta and shells in bottom of casserole dish; add crumbled hamburger.
Next, pour spaghetti sauce to cover.
Add pepperoni slices and top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: candied nuts
directions: Melt butter in jelly-roll pan.
Add nuts and beaten mixture of egg whites and sugar.
Put into 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Cook elbow macaroni.
Drain, rinse and return to pot.
Using frying pan, saute garlic in oil.
Add ground beef; brown meat. Drain any fat.
Add meat, along with sauce and Cheez Whiz to cooked macaroni.
Heat until cheese is melted into the sauce. Serve with grated cheese on top.

title: a recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Start with love, a generous share, then blend in warmth and laughter.
Add lots of happy memories that will last forever after...
Don't forget the patience, for the days when things go wrong.
Add a sense of humor and a faith that's deep and strong. Garnish with some compliments lovingly expressed, and there you have the recipe for marriage at its best!

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix mayo, soup, eggs, cheese and onion. Mix well. Place broccoli in casserole dish. Pour mixture over broccoli and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 min.

title: oat bran blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in muffin pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
(Moist and fruity!)

title: prune cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Sift flour and spices together; add to egg mixture.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: lemony wine cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine wine, sugar and lemon juice; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, arrange fruit and ice in glasses.
Add club soda to chilled mixture and pour over fruit and ice. Makes about 7 cups.

title: banana nut bread i
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, oil, egg and mashed banana.
In a separate bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to the banana mixture, a small amount at a time.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve with butter, softened cream cheese or peanut butter.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Add onion and green onion to margarine, cook until soft.
Stir in pumpkin, chicken stock, bay leaf, sugar, curry powder, nutmeg and parsley.
Cook 15 minutes, uncovered.
Puree in blender.
Add milk and salt gradually, mix and simmer 10 minutes.
Garnish with chopped green peppers or a drop of sour cream or paprika.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch dish. Pour chopped chicken in dish. Mix soup and sour cream together and spread over chicken. Melt margarine and mix with crushed cracker crumbs. Sprinkle with poppy seeds. Bake 350° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cook rice.
Add cheese to hot rice.
Add broccoli and soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave on High until set.

title: lasagna pizza
directions: Mix noodles, beef, pizza sauce and mushrooms; put in deep dish pizza pan or casserole dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: simple lasagna
directions: Boil noodles as directed. Brown hamburger. Season with salt and pepper. Drain off grease.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, Cool Whip and milk in a bowl.
Spread in pie crust.
Store in freezer.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a casserole dish.
Layer chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers over top.
Drizzle melted margarine over crackers.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Make Oreos into crumbs by putting into blender.
(Put cookies in 3 or 4 at a time because it's easier to blend.) Press into pie pans.
Soften ice cream.
Add creme de menthe.
Mix well.
Add green food coloring if desired.
Pour into crusts.
Freeze overnight.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.
You can garnish top by adding some of the Oreo crumbs.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use as a spread on crackers or Pepperidge Farm mini bread slices.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and transfer to a 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: baked eggs
directions: Beat eggs, mustard and milk, fold in ham, bread, salt and cheese.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with foil, bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate-walnut puffs
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add dash of salt.
Gradually add sugar to beaten eggs. Add vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in melted chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Remove at once to racks to cool.

title: milk cupcakes(portuguese)
directions: Mix the sugar with the eggs, then add the flour, melted butter, lemon and the milk.
Sprinkle the mold with butter and sugar.
(You can cut on the sugar and butter.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: gingered beef and pineapple stir-fry
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Cut steak lengthwise with grain into 1/4-inch slices; cut slices in half crosswise.
Combine steak and next 5 ingredients in a large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Seal bag and marinate in refrigerator 2 hours, turning bag occasionally. Remove steak from bag; discard marinade.

title: rice pudding
directions: You will need a 12 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex pan.

title: walnut cranberry relish
directions: Drop walnuts into rapidly boiling water; boil 3 minutes. Drain well.
Spread on flat baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until crisp and very lightly browned.
Cool and chop.

title: three apples of the land
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Rub the pan with garlic clove; discard clove.
Layer the potatoes, apples, cheese and horseradish in that order, seasoning with salt and pepper. Repeat, finishing last layer with grated cheese.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in the boiling water.
Add 7-Up and chill until it molds off the spoon, then add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Let set in a large flat Pyrex dish (7 x 10-inch).

title: lucille's fruit salad
directions: Mix cut up fruit with Cool Whip. For decoration, top with cherries that have been drained and dried, also nuts if desired.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar, butter or margarine and eggs.
Add flour one cup at a time, mix well.
Add vanilla and mix; add 7-Up last.
Beat for 20 minutes; pour into tube cake pan. Do not grease or flour the pan.
Bake for 45 minutes for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
When cake is done, loosen with knife around edges.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 1/2 hour.
Loosen again, put cake on serving dish and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: taco soup
directions: In large Dutch oven or kettle, brown beef and onion.
Drain any fat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: company corn
directions: Mix all together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pecan pumpkin cake
directions: Beat together crushed vanilla wafers, chopped pecans and 3/4 cup softened butter and press evenly onto bottom of 3 greased round cake pans.
Combine thoroughly pumpkin, spice cake mix, eggs and 1/4 cup softened butter.
Spread batter evenly over the 3 cake pans lined with crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Mix powdered sugar, 2/3 cup softened butter, cream cheese and vanilla.
This is the filling.
On serving plate, layer the 3 cakes (nut and crumb mixture side down) with 1/2 cup filling spread between each layer.
Frost sides and layer; spread 1/4 cup caramel topping on top.
Arrange pecan halves on cake and serve.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix at lowest speed until dough forms balls.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edges.
Let cool.

title: shortbread cookie
directions: Place butter and sugar in the bowl of an electric mixer.
Mix on low speed for 15 seconds.
Add flour and salt.
Continue mixing on low speed for 3 to 5 minutes until dough comes together.
It will look dry just before it comes together.
Place the dough on a lightly floured board.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out dough until a 3-inch star cutter or other shape cookie shape.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in order given and spread in pan, 9 x 9-inch.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 20 servings.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Can prepare 2 to 3 hours in advance.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: country supper soup
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Place all main ingredients (first 11 ingredients) together in a large soup kettle and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and continue simmering for another 1/2 hour.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: bread pudding for a crowd
directions: Butter bread and place buttered side down in a greased cake pan (9 x 13-inch, 6 slices per layer).
Combine milk, sugar, salt and eggs.
Pour over bread.
With large spoon, press bread down just enough to make sure all the bread gets the milk mixture over them.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes covered then 1/2 hour uncovered.
If raisins are desired, sprinkle some between layers.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Place broccoli and margarine in bowl in microwave for 1 minute.
Beat eggs; stir in cottage cheese.
Stir in broccoli and margarine; mix well.
Add corn muffin mix; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°, or until brown.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix in crushed vanilla wafers and milk.
Add pecans.
Bake in a Bundt or angel food cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: wiener daffle
directions: Cut
wieners;
set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in pot and cook until mixture is hot and well mixed.
Add wieners and cook until they are done, about 10 minutes; enjoy.

title: family salisbury steaks
directions: Mix together all ingredients like any meat loaf.
(Substitute ingredients as you wish, but try and keep it on the spicy side). Shape into burger patties and brown well on both sides in large skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Cover patties with Heinz brown canned gravy.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: best garlic bread
directions: Blend butter or margarine with garlic and honey.
Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Spread butter mixture thickly on both cut sides of bread.
Sprinkle lightly with basil, then paprika.
Put loaf back together and coat lightly with olive oil.
Wrap in foil and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Slice in large hunks and serve hot.

title: easy turkey and stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package directions. Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spray casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray. Spoon stuffing mixture into dish and press it across bottom and up sides to form a shell.
Combine soup, milk, turkey and peas.
Pour into stuffing shell. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Heat oil in pan. Add the onion, red pepper and garlic. Saute until softened. Add the meat and saute
until browned. If desired, transfer the cooked mixture to a food processor and chop for a few seconds on the pulse setting. Transfer the meat
to a saucepan and add the stock, parsley, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce. Add mushrooms. Cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes.

title: gems
directions: Add sugar and melted shortening to beaten egg.
Then add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Drop by tablespoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
We have these for breakfast with butter, oleo or jelly.
I am told they are similar to English scones.
They are a favorite of our family.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Mix marshmallows, Rice Krispies and peanut butter together.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool, then cut into pieces.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix 3 minutes
on
medium speed.
Bake at 350° in Bundt pan for 35 to 45 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: mound cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed on box.
Then bring to a boil the milk, sugar and marshmallow cream and boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and add coconut.
Pour this mixture over warm cake.
Mix chocolate pieces and oleo and melt over low heat.
Pour this mixture over coconut that is on cake.
Refrigerate 3 hours until chocolate is set.

title: cherry icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, nuts, cherries and coconut.
Blend in flour by hand.
Divide dough into 2 rolls (roll in reserved coconut).
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Cook sugar, dates, eggs and oleo in skillet slowly for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat to let cool until you can handle.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
(You can handle this mixture best if you grease your fingers with vegetable oil.)
Roll in a small ball and roll in Snow Flake coconut.

title: tostado
directions: Position oven rack in upper third of oven and preheat to very hot (450°).
Crumble beef into large heavy skillet and place over moderately high heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook 5 to 8 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Add cumin, oregano, salt, pepper and flour.
Stir over medium heat for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and chilies; cook for 3 minutes or until thickened.

title: peanut patty
directions: Bring sugar, water and corn syrup to a boil.
Add peanuts and food coloring.
Cook to hard-boil stage.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and a pinch of salt.
Beat until thick.
Pour into greased muffin tins or onto greased cookie sheet.
Let set.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Slice chicken breast thin; pound it to loosen it.
Roll in flour with pepper and paprika.
Saute in garlic and margarine (brown it) until cooked; then sprinkle coarse pepper on top.
Serve with rice and green beans or mixed vegetables.

title: granny's sugar cookies("this is a good rolled cookie for cookie cutter.")
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and egg.
Sift together and add the salt, baking powder and flour.
Blend in the vanilla.
Roll out; cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw frozen broccoli according to directions on package. Mix soup and milk together. Add all ingredients to thawed broccoli. Lightly mix and pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Mixture bubbles up as it is baking. Make sure dish is large enough.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all together with blender.
Add 2 tablespoons or more (to taste) to one cup of boiling water.

title: ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beat until thickened.
Add whipping cream, vanilla and salt and mix thoroughly.
Pour into can, add milk to fill line on can and stir well.
Freeze as directed.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry hamburg with onion. Layer casserole dish with cabbage, hamburg-onion and cabbage.
Top with tomato soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain
the liquid from the oysters and mix it with half and half;
season
with
salt
and
pepper and a few drops of Tabasco. Butter
an
x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Crumb 1/2-inch crackers
in bottom of dish.
Put in a layer of oysters.
Pour 1/2
liquid over
this
and dot with butter.
Put in 1/4-inch layer
of crackers,
a layer of oysters and remaining liquid. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with finely crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix baking soda with buttermilk and add with the rest of the ingredients to creamed butter and sugar. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cottage pudding with lemon sauce
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Beat together the butter, sugar, egg and lemon extract.
Add flour and milk alternately; beat each time.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Place casserole in baking pan.
Pour very hot water into pan to a depth of about 1-inch.
Bake until knife inserted 1-inch from edge of casserole comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Center will be soft but will set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: summer squash mess
directions: Peel and sliced squash.
Parboil for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Slice onion and mushrooms.
Saute in butter until limp.
Add the tomatoes and cheese.
Add all to squash and cover with buttered crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken base(microwave)
directions: In 3-quart casserole dish, combine chicken, celery, garlic and ginger.
Cover with lid; microwave on High 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in broth and water.
Cover; microwave on High 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine oleo, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in bits and nuts. Spread into a greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and fry in deep fryer. Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain and cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, soup and beaten eggs.
Add broccoli to cheese mixture and place in buttered baking dish.
Top with crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Beat in eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour in lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and walnuts together.
Sprinkle over cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Ice cake while hot.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in 13 x 9-inch glass dish in order given.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with Tostitos, Doritos, dip style.

title: cereal cheese stars
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Roll on lightly floured board and cut with small cookie cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mama's beef roast
directions: Place frozen roast on bottom of roasting pan or extra large pot (larger than Dutch oven).
Then add vegetables all around roast and on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Then cover with lid or extra heavy duty foil and cook in oven at 500° about 20 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 250° and cook all night.
If oven cooks fast, you may want to reduce heat to 200°.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Simmer cranberries, sugar, raisins, spice and water in 2-quart saucepan (uncovered) over medium heat, stirring frequently until juice is released from cranberries, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered until thick, about 15 minutes.
Refrigerate covered, up to 2 weeks.

title: no bake ice cream(coffee can method)
directions: You will need one 3-pound coffee can, one 1-pound coffee can, ice and rock salt.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, salt and cinammon:
set aside. Cream butter or margarine and brown sugar 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat in molasses. Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Chill dough until firm (1 to 2 hours).
Preheat oven 375°.
Divide dough into fourths.
Working one fourth at a time, roll on floured pastry cloth to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut with desired shaped cookie cutters. Gently transfer cutouts to ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Cool slightly before removing.
Decorate as desired.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain and reserve liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth, but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add vegetable liquor and milk slowly, stirring to avoid lumps.
Add seasonings and cheese, cut in small pieces. Stir until melted.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Put in casserole dish (flavor is improved if refrigerated overnight).
Heat in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Sprinkle fried onions over casserole and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix hot water, 1/2 c. sugar and shortening; let cool. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add to cool mixture well beaten eggs and unsifted flour; mix well.
Put in greased bowl and let rise overnight.
Work down.
Cut out biscuits and let rise again.
Bake.
Put butter on half of biscuit.
Fold over and pinch edges together.
Bake at 400° until finished.

title: hearty ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce leaves; mix well. Chill 2 or 3 hours before serving.
Serve on lettuce, if desired. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange-pecan bread
directions: Combine egg, orange, raisins, rind, shortening and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar into orange mixture; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a well-greased 5 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325 to 350° for 1 hour, or longer (check with a toothpick at 1 hour).

title: irish lettuce salad
directions: Mix together.
Pour on dressing just before serving.

title: mexican chef's salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes
and
lettuce;
toss
with cheese, dressing, hot sauce or
taco
sauce,
and taco seasoning salt. Crunch and add Doritos.
Slice
and add avocado.
Brown ground beef; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add kidney beans and cook 10 minutes.
Mix all together and serve hot or cold.

title: speedy pizzas
directions: Split the English muffins with a fork.
Toast the muffin halves.
Spread muffins with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle each with a pinch of oregano.
Cover with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts. Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and pineapple (with juice).
Toss bread cubes in to moisten.
Put into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Bake roast beef; shred into pieces.
Using the broth from the roast, dump into it the carrots, celery, meat, onions and potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
When vegetables are tender, add the gravy mixes.
You may need to add water to broth if there is not enough to cover vegetables.
Let simmer until desired thickness.

title: marvelous kugel
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Put remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend until well mixed.
Mix with noodles.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese; cook 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly until it melts.
Mix vegetables and fettuccine. Pour cheese sauce over mixture; toss well to coat.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, fresh parsley and pepper.
Makes 4 servings, each with 10 grams fat.

title: cornbread cakes
directions: Mix ingredients and fry as you would pancakes. Turn only once when brown on one side. Then flip to the other side. Will make about 8 cakes.

title: pineapple party salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple.
Add enough water to syrup to make 2 cups.
Heat to boiling point.
Dissolve lemon and lime gelatin in boiling liquid.
Add salt.
Cool until slightly thickened. When beginning to congeal, fold in cottage cheese, mayonnaise, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold or 9-inch square pan. Place in refrigerator to chill and set.
Serve on lettuce leaf, topped with a touch of mayonnaise.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter and remove from heat.
Add sugar and stir well. Add eggs and stir well.
Add all dry ingredients plus milk and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly and add chips.
Blend well.
Spread mixture in oblong pan (9 x 13-inch), well greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: wedding bell punch
directions: Ice cream and sherbet need to be soft.
(See tips on making punch.)
Blend cold lemonade and orange juice with soft vanilla ice cream and pineapple sherbet.

title: chicken breasts with sour cream(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Coat chicken with next 7 ingredients mixed together.
Place in buttered dish and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and place a pat of butter on each chicken breast.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.
(Boneless chicken breasts may be used but reduce baking time approximately 15 minutes to prevent drying and overbaking.)
Garnish with lemon slice and sprig of parsley for a company meal of which you can be proud.

title: blueberry special
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs, chopped pecans and powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, granulated sugar and lemon juice.
Pour into shell. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with 1 can of blueberry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hassan's steak marinade
directions: Combine
these	ingredients in pan or bowl large enough to hold
steak.
Place steak in marinade and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours,
turning
occasionally.
Makes porterhouse, T-bone, etc., "mouthwatering good" when cooked over coals.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute leeks, onions and garlic in oil and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and 6 cups of water.
Simmer for 2 hours, covered.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil, powdered sugar and white sugar together.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar together and add to first mixture.
Mix well to form dough.
Roll dough by teaspoon to form a ball.
Roll in sugar (sometimes I add cinnamon to sugar).
Place on greased
cookie sheet.
Press down with a small glass.
Bake about 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: blueberry nut torte
directions: To make the crust, mix together flour, 1/2 c. walnuts, graham cracker crumbs and butter. Press into an 8 inch square pan or quiche dish. Bake 5 minutes at 350°. Cool. To make the filling, cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add whipped topping and mix with cream mixture until frothy. Turn into cooled crust and refrigerate for 20 minutes or until cream cheese mixture is firm. Sprinkle with walnuts. Top with can of blueberry pie filling. Return to refrigerator and chill until ready to serve. Makes 10 servings.

title: crunchy creamy spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Stir in sour cream.
Turn into serving dish.
Top with onion rings.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix coffee and syrup. Mash 1/2 of ice cream and add to coffee and syrup. Stir. Just before serving, add soda water. Pour into chilled punch bowl. May use ice block to keep cold. Top with spoonfuls of remaining ice cream.

title: crustless omelette
directions: Butter	glass
pie pan and line with the cheese slices. Beat eggs with fork; add milk and 8 of the bacon slices which have been
broken
up.
Pour over the cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
About 10 minutes before done baking, add 4 slices
of bacon which you curl when you take off the stove. Let dish stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken pieces in margarine and garlic powder.
Sprinkle with Italian herbs.
Cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes until tender.
Prepare Cacciatore Sauce according to recipe.
Serve hot sauce over chicken, accompanied by rice or noodles.
Makes 5 servings.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pumpkin mix.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.

title: dirty white trash
directions: Mix raisins, peanuts, pecans and Golden Grahams.
Melt in microwave:
chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over first mixture and mix well.
Pour confectioners sugar in a large sack. Put the mixture in on top of the sugar and shake to cover it all.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, salt, nutmeg and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and milk, then stir in dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: jimmy carter dessert
directions: Layer #1:
Mix together oleo, flour and peanuts.
Put in cake pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in pan.
