directions: In a large bowl, mix first five ingredients.
In a small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Then mix together with top ingredients.
Serve cold.
Serves 10.

title: creole cauliflower au gratin
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; add onion and green pepper and brown lightly.
Blend in flour and add tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling point and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cauliflower and heat thoroughly.
Place mixture in a casserole and cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and mixture is hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain fat off.
Add remaining ingredients.
Warm 10 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Mash up.
Then put everything but 1/2 stick of butter in it.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Then pour 1/2 stick butter on top.
Grate cheese and put on top.
Melt it in the oven.

title: macaroni and cheese(crock-pot)
directions: Put all sauce ingredients in crock-pot; stir well.
Cover; cook on high 1 hour.
Add cooked, drained macaroni.
Cover; cook on low 3 hours, or until done.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add milk, flour, poppy seed and almond.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and refrigerate in plastic or jars.

title: taco salad
directions: *Can use 3/4 cup water, 2 tablespoons minced onion, 2 tablespoons chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon cumin, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and dash of hot pepper sauce in place of taco seasoning packet.

title: freezer corn
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool. Put in freezer bags.
Freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar & vinegar; mix well. Refrigerate dressing about 3 hours. Fry bacon and crumble. Trim broccoli, using only florets. Add pecans, raisins and onions to broccoli. Mix with dressing when ready to serve. Serves 12.

title: tabouli
directions: Place the bulgur with cold water to cover in a large bowl. Set aside for 30 minutes, until most of water is absorbed.
Drain the bulgur, squeezing out excess water.
Toss the moist bulgur with all the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well together the beef, pork sausage, onion, salt, pepper and eggs.
Use 1 to 1 1/2 packages of soda crackers or 1 to 1 1/2 cups oatmeal.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 mixture into loaf pan.
Put shredded cheese desired on top.
Top with the rest of meat mixture. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican artichoke dip (spread)
directions: Line an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with mashed green chilies. Then fill the dish with a mixture of the remaining ingredients. Bake for 30 minutes at 325° until browned.
Good with corn chips or crackers.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine yeast and 2 cups of flour.
Heat milk, sugar, salt and butter/margarine.
Add to flour mixture. Add egg and
beat
at
low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat at high speed for 3
minutes.
Gradually add the remaining 1 1/2 cups flour and continuing
mixing
by
hand
to form a soft dough. Turn dough into
a
greased
bowl
in a warm place, 80 to 85°. Dough should double in volume in 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn dough on floured board and shape.
Place on greased baking sheet or muffin tin. Cover
for 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mama's layer cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at the time, except 2 of the whites.
Add flour with baking powder mixed in, and then add milk with vanilla mixed in.
Mix well and put batter in 4 cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until slightly brown at 350°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Stir in brown sugar; spread evenly in the pan.
Drain pineapple.
Arrange the pineapple slices on the top of the sugar and butter mixture.
Place a cherry in the center of each ring.
Gently spread crushed pineapple over the top.
Set aside.

title: knox blocks(finger jello)
directions: Mix gelatine and jello.
Add boiling water and dissolve.
Add whipping cream.
Pour into pan and refrigerate until set.

title: prize cookies
directions: Pre-heat over to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoons, 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes until lightly browned. Cool.
Frost if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: First roll nuts in a little of the flour, then sift rest of flour and other dry ingredients.
Beat eggs slightly and add to oil, then add all other ingredients.
Gradually add sifted ingredients to egg-oil mixture, stirring well after each addition. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in tube pan.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: kids slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for 2-5 minutes. Put in ice cream pail and add all three flavors of juice. Freeze 12-24 hours, stirring every 3 hours. The next day scoop into cup and add a little 7up. Stir and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes, celery and onions.
Put in large soup pot and cover with water; cook until tender and water has cooked down a little.
Add milk, noodles and butter.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: fish casserole
directions: Melt butter; add cracker crumbs and egg.
Mix fish into mixture.
Bake 15 minutes, covered, at 375°, and 15 minutes, uncovered.
You can baste with wine!

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Grease bottom and sides of oblong baking dish.
Mix blackberries with 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Work shortening into dry ingredients.
Work 3/4 cup cold water into mixture.
Divide dough in half and roll out.
Lay bottom dough in greased pan; prick dough.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour over crust.
Pour in berries; dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle another 1/4 cup flour over berries.
Lay top dough over this; pierce it.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and salt in 3-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat until a soft ball (234°) is formed.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.
Score while still warm.

title: fried rice
directions: Optional:
Omit bacon bits and add 1 1/2 to 2 cups of cooked chicken.

title: the "no guilt" fruitcake treat
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 large heavy weight cookie sheets with cooking spray or line mini-muffin tins with paper liners, spray with cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: slow-cooked breen beans with tomatoes
directions: Drain the tomatoes, reserving the juice. Remove the stem ends from the tomatoes and seed, if desired. Break the tomatoes into chunks.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Cool, peel and slice thin.
Fry bacon until crisp; add onion and cook 1 minute more. Blend in flour, salt, sugar and pepper.
Stir in vinegar and water; cook, stirring, 10 minutes.
Pour over sliced potatoes; add celery seed and parsley.
Serve at once.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 sugar over fruit and set aside.
Combine remaining sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour mixture into dish.
Add fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Chop asparagus and set aside.
Sprinkle gelatin over water in a small saucepan; let stand for 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat until gelatin dissolves, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour into container of electric blender.
Add reserved liquid, lemon juice, mayonnaise, cream cheese and onion; blend until smooth.
Stir in pecans and asparagus and spoon into an 8-inch square pan.
Cover and chill until firm.
Cut into 9 squares and serve on lettuce. Yield: 9 servings, 100 calories per serving.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese,
1 cup Cheddar cheese and 3 tablespoons of the onion and garlic.
Spread into bottom of 9-inch pie plate. Mix salsa and tomato; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Cheddar cheese and remaining 1 tablespoon onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients. Bake in five 1 pound coffee cans. Divide batter evenly. Should be about half full.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all and place in a 9-inch casserole dish, sprayed with Pam or greased.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(For larger casserole, use a 16 ounce package of vegetables, 1 1/2 cans of soup and 3/4 pint of sour cream.)

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla alternately with baking powder and flour.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll half of pastry and fit into pie pan.
Mix concentrate, tapioca, spices, salt and apples.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with remaining pie crust.
Make slits in top crust.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tiger fudge
directions: Melt the white chocolate and peanut butter; pour into greased cookie sheet.
Melt the chocolate bar.
Pour onto first mixture in 3 strips, then swirl.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pam a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place bread on bottom in a single layer.
Sprinkle meat, then cheese over bread.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over casserole.
Blend cornflakes and margarine and spread over top of casserole.
Let stand in fridge overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package.
Roll out for a 9-inch, 2 crust pie.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Combine meat, milk, soup mix, pepper and allspice.
Pat into pie plate.
Put on top crust; flute edge.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine together.
Add sugar gradually and eggs, beating after each addition.
Add flour gradually and extract.
Beat well.

title: fruit whip-up
directions: In medium bowl, combine fruit cocktail (undrained) and pudding; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Keep cool until ready to serve.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix well ingredients, except prunes and nuts. Add prunes and nuts; mix and pour into 9 x 13 glass pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Before cake cools, make holes in top of cake with toothpick.

title: diabetic drop cookies
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend oleo, sugar and salt; add eggs and peanut butter.
Stir in flour sifted with soda.
Form dough into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork in both directions (#). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork chops with peas and tomatoes
directions: Cook chops in large heavy skillet over medium heat, turning once every 5 minutes until done and fat is partially rendered. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon sage and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables per package directions; drain.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add flour.
Gradually add milk; stir constantly until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Add spices and 1 cup of cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Spoon sauce over vegetables; toss to coat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and almonds.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix the 3 soups, milk and stick of butter.
Heat until butter melts. Pour 1/2 mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice into soup mixture and stir, spreading evenly into pan.
Lay chicken strips onto rice and soup mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over chicken. Sprinkle heavily with Parmesan and almonds. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Brown beef, season to taste (no need to brown pepperoni). Drain well. Grease lightly and dust with flour a 12 to 14 inch pizza pan or a 15 x 10 jelly roll pan. Combine flour, oregano, pepper, eggs and milk. Mix until smooth. Pour batter in pan. Tilt pan so batter covers bottom. Arrange meat any other toppings you wish to have, and bake at 350 degrees until crust is golden brown.

title: magic chocolate crackle bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan (or square one); set aside. In medium bowl, combine flour with 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Add egg yolks; mix well. Cut in shortening and 1 ounce chocolate until crumbly. Firmly press into greased pan. Bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: 100% natural wheat germ bread
directions: Mix dry yeast, sugar and warm water; let stand until bubbly. In bowl, mix brown sugar/honey, milk, salt, oil, 2 cups flour and wheat germ together.
Add yeast mixture to be followed by 2 more cups flour.
Beat with spoon until mixed.
Put in 2 (1 pound) coffee cans (greased).
Let rise until top of cans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool; remove from cans.
Keep refrigerated. Enjoy; best when toasted.

title: angel salad
directions: Reserve some pineapple juice.
Add all ingredients except pineapple.
Cook and let thicken.
Add pineapple (crushed), pecans, marshmallows and cherries.
Then fold in Cool Whip.

title: delicious party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Sprite, together.
Place in freezer.
When ready to serve, pour Sprite over punch mixture. Dilute to taste.
Serve slushy.
Serves about 50 plus.

title: snickerdoodle drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, beat together butter, brown sugar and 3/4 cup granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture; mix well.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil zucchini 6 minutes or until clear and drain.
May have to squeeze.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil hard for 6 minutes.
Remove form heat and add jello.

title: baked barbecue chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly; dry with paper towel.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Spread evenly. Sprinkle onion and celery over top of barbecue sauce; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, milk, cream, butter, vanilla and nutmeg; blend well.
Pour mixture over bread slices, turning until saturated.
Arrange into lightly greased 4-quart dish.
Pour excess over bread.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with warm syrup or fruit preserves.
Serves 10.

title: pull later taffy
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart pan.
Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Add butter; cook over medium heat until it boils and sugar dissolves (stir constantly).
Attach candy thermometer. Cook to 248°, no stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in extract and coloring.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
With buttered hands, roll into ball.
Return to pan.
When cold, wrap in plastic wrap.
Store up to 2 weeks at room temperature.

title: amish cheerios squares
directions: Butter 9-inch square pan.
In a large saucepan, blend jello, syrup and butter.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Cheerios.
Spread mixture in pan and let set about 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: icebox banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Mix in Eagle Brand
and Cool Whip.
In 9 x 13-inch dish, layer the cookies, 1/2 bananas, 1/2 mixture, then repeat.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix with 2 eggs and melted margarine (butter may be used).
Batter will be thick.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; top with mixture of remaining 2 eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
If desired, coconut and nuts may be added to batter in amount preferred.
Cuts into squares or pieces easier when warm.

title: cheese pineapple salad
directions: Top pineapple with cheese.
Top with mayonnaise.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Combine flour, sugar, margarine and salt.
Stir until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly in pan.
Bake until lightly golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Prepare filling and pour over baked layer.
Spread evenly.
Bake until filling is set, about 20 minutes. Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Makes 70 squares.

title: oven onion potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large plastic bag, mix all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until all potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a greased shallow baking dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally, approximately 40 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Potatoes will stick if not stirred.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a pan over medium heat, melt the chocolate chips, butter or margarine and the peanut butter.
Pour the box of cereal in a large bowl or dishpan.
Pour the chocolate mixture over the cereal.
Mix well to coat the cereal.
Put the powdered sugar in a doubled grocery sack.
Dump in the cereal.
Shake well to coat. Store any leftover in an airtight container.

title: carol's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Add garlic powder, oregano, tomato paste and hot water.
Simmer.
Layer cottage cheese, sauce, cooked lasagna noodles and Mozzarella cheese.

title: sausage souffle for breakfast
directions: Slightly butter a cake pan.
Break bread into small pieces. Layer in the cheese on top of bread.
Boil sausage, then in a frying pan, brown sausage.
Cut sausage into thirds.
Layer over cheese in pan.
Beat eggs, milk and dry mustard together, then pour over ingredients in pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix juice.
When ready to serve, add to your punch bowl.
Put one scoop of ice cream into serving glass and add ginger ale. Stir.
You can make this up as you need it.

title: cookies and cream ice cream
directions: Set ice cream and Cool Whip out to soften.
Crush Oreos into very small pieces.
Mix together and place in a freezer-safe container.
Cover with foil.
This is an easy summer treat.

title: francaise'
directions: Saute chopped onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add Italian spices.
Add rest of ingredients.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: edinberg squares
directions: Cream together oil and brown sugar.
Add oats and flour. Divide this mixture in half.
Press one half of the mixture on the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Put in thickened fruit. Sprinkle the rest of the crumble mixture on top of the thickened fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frying pan. Add green chilies. Add cans of tomato sauce, sour cream, seasonings and 1/2 pound of cheese. (Use 1/2 of cheese in meat mixture; set other half aside.) Simmer for 20 minutes over low heat. Take tortillas and cover bottom of 13 x 15-inch pan. Add layer of meat, then another layer of tortillas and rest of meat. Take other half of cheese (grated) and put on top of meat mixture. Bake until cheese is melted for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: instant mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour into blender.
Add all other ingredients and blend at high speed for 5 to 10 seconds. Pour into bowl and refrigerate for 5 minutes or longer.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in ungreased casserole. Crush crackers; mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly around edges and light brown on top.
Serve while warm.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Heat Karo syrup and sugar until it comes to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Take off of burner.
Add Rice Krispies.
Place in a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.

title: pasta salad for a crowd
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on box.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss with pasta.
Chill and serve.

title: southern fried baked steak
directions: Pound steak to tenderize; cut into serving size pieces. Season with salt and pepper.
Dust with flour.
Combine milk and egg; dip meat into egg mixture and back into flour.
In a skillet, brown meat on both sides in oil.
Place onion in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place meat over onion.
Pour broth over all.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peach-banana dessert
directions: Drain peaches, measuring syrup.
Add enough water to measure 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add liquid.
Pour into individual dessert dishes; add peaches and bananas.
Chill until set.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: pecan pie mini muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and pecans. Add remaining ingredients. Lightly spray mini-muffin pan with cooking spray and fill 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. If using a dark pan, bake at 325°.

title: cherry pie mix cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie filling.
Spread 3/4 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour on pie filling.
Drop remaining batter on pie filling.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
While warm, drizzle with powdered sugar frosting.

title: durgin park corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, beat the sugar and eggs until light.
Stir together salt, flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
Add to bowl along with butter and milk.
Beat together quickly.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix well.
Fold in a 2 pound bag frozen hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar, add the eggs, one at a time, and continue to cream mixture.
Add almond extract. Mix in flour and baking powder.
Turn mixture into greased and floured 9-inch spring-form pan or equivalent.
Arrange peach slices on dough.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar.
Serve with fruits.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put salmon, 1/4 cup water and remaining ingredients into a bowl.
Mix to blend. Spray loaf pan with cooking spray.
Place mixture in pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until golden.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: crazy salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir dry gelatin into cottage cheese and mix well.
Add drained pineapple and whipped topping. Fold until all ingredients are mixed.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until serving time. Can be served as a salad on lettuce or as a dessert topped with some reserved whipped topping and a cherry.

title: grandma libey's banana cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, soda and baking powder. Alternately add flour and milk to mixture.
Next, stir in bananas and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Ice with caramel icing.

title: deep-fried stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and trim stems slightly.
Remove stems from mushrooms; set caps aside.
Finely chop stems.
In small saucepan, combine chopped stems, 1 tablespoon butter, onion, parsley flakes, chives, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mushrooms are tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Fill caps with stuffing mixture, packing firmly and mounding mixture slightly.

title: mic crighton's freezer corn
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Stir, then bake for 10 minutes.
Cool and bag for freezer.

title: paula's favorite reese's cookies
directions: Cream shortening or butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
If colored play dough is desired, add color to water before mixing.
If scented play dough is desired, use peppermint extract.
Heat over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes away from side of pan.
Let cool and have children knead until smooth.
Add a little more flour while kneading if it is sticky.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken.
Place cooked and drained spaghetti in a baking dish.
Layer deboned and chopped chicken on spaghetti.
Mix chicken soup and mushroom soup together and layer on top of chicken.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: yum yum
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and form dough.
Press into bottom of lasagna dish.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly golden.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar and spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk together and pour over.
Top with Cool Whip spreading evenly.
Refrigerate until served.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cheesecake
directions: Mix flour, butter, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla together in food processor.
Press dough into 10-inch spring-form pan, making sure it goes up the sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
While cooling mix cream cheese, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla together.
Spread on cooled crust.
Pare and slice apples thin.
Toss with remaining sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and walnuts.
Arrange topping attractively on top of filling.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 4 to 6 hours.
Best served at room temperature.

title: sundae brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prick bottom and sides of pie crust with fork.
Bake crust 10 minutes; remove from oven.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs; stir in sugar and butter.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and nuts.
Pour into pie crust; return to oven.
Bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set.
(Pie will not test done in center.)
Serve warm or cool with ice cream; drizzle with topping.
Garnish with a Hershey's Kiss.

title: chops and potatoes
directions: Arrange sliced potatoes in greased dish or pan.
Dot with butter.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour milk over all.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake only 15 minutes.

title: christmas dough ornaments
directions: Add water until thick (like cookie dough).
Knead until you get all bubbles out.
Bake at 325° until brown (maybe 1 hour or so).
Decorate.

title: ginger beef
directions: In chopping bowl, combine onions, garlic, turmeric, chili peppers, ginger and salt; chop fine.
Add flank steak slices or strips and toss together.
Let stand to season; refrigerate from 15 minutes to 3 hours, depending on your schedule.
Then, in a Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add flank steak and onion mixture; brown lightly.
Add tomatoes, then cook, uncovered, over high heat for 10 minutes.
Add soup; cover and simmer 1 hour if steak is sliced or 1 1/2 to 2 hours if it's in strips or until steak is tender.

title: hibiscus cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients and mix.
Combine egg whites, yolks, orange zest and orange juice.
Add to dry mixture. Set aside for 20 to 30 minutes.
Lightly grease a baking sheet and mark 5-inch circles on the surface.
Drop a spoonful of batter in each circle.
Spread evenly to cover the area.
Prepare and bake only one sheet at a time. Bake until the edges are a light brown, but the center is soft (5 to 6 minutes). Quickly remove cookies from the pan with a spatula.
Mold cookies around orange to create cupped shapes.
Once shaped, cool on rack.
Fill with fresh fruit, ice cream or pudding.

title: chocolate snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt with fork in ungreased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: yam bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all the ingredients.
Divide into greased bread pans and bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick picante sauce
directions: Remove seeds and veins from peppers.
Place peppers, onions and stewed tomatoes in food processor and chop to desired consistency.
In large container combine tomato mixture and Italian dressing.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Add buttermilk. Fold in beaten egg whites. Fill one 9 in. unbaked pie crust and bake at 325 degrees for one hour.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill. Will keep for several weeks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: fish stew
directions: Dice fatback and fry until crisp.
Dice onions and cook in fatback grease until brown.
Prepare this over medium heat.
Add soup, water, ketchup, Texas Pete, butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add fillet of flounder and allow to cook about 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: cabbage, meat and rice casserole
directions: Place cabbage in a greased 2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle rice on top.
Crumble ground beef over top.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan; heat to boiling.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Place the pastry in a baking dish.
Brown meat and drain well. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in prepared crust.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Next place Veg-All.
Mix chicken soup and broth together.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour, milk and margarine together.
Spoon over chicken mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° until brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Clean broccoli, remove stems and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender; do not drain.
Set aside.
If using frozen broccoli, not necessary to thaw.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour; cook for 3 to 4 minutes. Add chicken stock; stir and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low. Add half and half, cheese and broccoli.
Heat until cheese melts. Do not boil.

title: california chicken
directions: Sprinkle onion soup over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice evenly in pan.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Dilute soup with water or broth.
Pour over chicken.
Dot with butter and bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown onions with ground beef.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook on high for 20 minutes, then on low for 10 minutes.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Cut as for French fries.
Put in stewer; cover with water.
Add salt and dust of pepper.
Cook on medium heat until tender.
Add corned beef and ground sage. Serves 4.

title: waterfront cooler
directions: Pour ingredients into a tall glass, stir well and serve over ice.

title: company cauliflower
directions: In shallow pan, toast sesame seed 10 minutes or until browned, shaking pan occasionally.
Rinse cauliflower and separate into small flowerets.
Cook in a 2-quart covered saucepan in 1-inch boiling, salted water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Place half of cauliflower in 1-quart casserole; season with salt and pepper.

title: golden brown chive roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel potatoes and place in a bowl of cold water until ready to use.
Dry thoroughly and cut a thin slice off the long side of each potato so it
can sit flat.
Cut vertical slits from the top almost to the bottom of each potato, being careful not to cut through it.
Dip the cut potatoes in melted butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Beat eggs; pour and mix with sugar mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat waffles
directions: Stir together dry ingredients with whisk or fork.
Separate the eggs and blend the yolks well with milk and canola oil. Lightly blend dry ingredients with the liquid ingredients until there are no lumps.
Beat egg whites until they peak and fold them into batter.
Bake in greased waffle iron until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix egg yolks and milk, then add dry ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.
Allow to cool, then pour in crust.
Beat egg whites; pour on pie and brown at 350°.

title: pear bread
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs, until blended.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients to wet; mix, stir and blend until smooth.
Add nuts and pears.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: rotel soup
directions: Cook meat in pan of water (about 3 cups); salt and pepper. Cook meat until done.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Add spaghetti about 1/2 hour before turning off soup. Cook soup for 1 to 2 hours on low.

title: italian baked chicken breasts
directions: Coat chicken breasts in Frying Magic.
In large skillet, heat oil and cook chicken about 7 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove from skillet and onto plate.
Steam broccoli spears and when done, add broccoli and garlic to same skillet.
Saute for 5 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, lay out broccoli spears. Place chicken breasts on top of spears and cheese slices on chicken.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Delicious.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in 325° oven as it heats.
Remove pan from oven and add crumbs.
Stir into butter. Pat out into even layer.
Sprinkle chips, coconut and nuts in evenly.
Carefully drizzle milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes until golden brown and when partially cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, ginger and salt.
Stir in chicken, grapes, celery, green onions and walnuts.
Cover; chill. Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix Bisquick with the milk. Spread into greased pie pan. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: rainbow cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.

title: lemon pudding cake(crock-pot)
directions: Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Beat yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add lemon peel, juice, butter and milk.
Combine dry ingredients and add to milk mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Spoon into slow cooker and cover.
Cook on high 2 to 3 hours.

title: awesome caramel brownies
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and pecans.
Stir until batter forms. Press 1/2 of the batter into pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: quick sugar cookies
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheets or spray with Pam.
Dip by teaspoon and roll in ball, then press with fork or roll in ball the size you want cookie to be and press with top of Pam can dipped in sugar.
You can also drop cookie from teaspoon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flour.
Add slightly beaten eggs, Karo and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake at 350° until set and brown.

title: peggy's brie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Place on top of Brie and sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake in oven or microwave until Brie is soft.
Serve with crackers.

title: spicy apple twists
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each apple into eight pieces. Unroll crescent rolls and separate into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half to make 16 triangles.
Place on apple piece at wide end and roll up.
Arrange in 9-inch square pan.
Drizzle with butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Pour orange juice or water into pan but not over dumplings.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until apples are tender.
Serve warm, plain or with cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the first two ingredients together until fluffy. Add the peanut butter and milk. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into the pie shells.

title: s-shaped cookies
directions: Mix sugar with eggs.
Make well and put in flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and butter.
Make balls and shape into s-shapes.
Bake at 350° on greased pan 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in shallow baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour flour mixture over margarine.
Pour peaches on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: raisin pecan tarts
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour; ball and divide into three parts.
Place in refrigerator for one hour.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine sugar and 3 cups water; bring to a boil.
Let cool. Add the rest of the ingredients and freeze.
Take out 2 hours before serving.

title: great grandma's potato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in all ingredients except flour.
Then add 5 cups flour.
Beat thoroughly. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Put in a greased bowl, turn greased side up. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down and divide into loaves or rolls.
Place in 2 to 3 greased loaf pans (or grease 1 cookie sheet for rolls).
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Brush tops with butter.
Yields 2 to 3 loaves.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° just a few minutes.
Next, mix filling of 2 soft sticks margarine, eggs, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat about 20 minutes with mixer.
Stir in 1 cup crushed pecans.
Spread on crumbs.
Next, layer bananas.
Next, layer well drained pineapple, then spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle a few nuts over Cool Whip.
Chill for 24 hours.
Decorate with cherries, if desired.

title: jansson's temptation(swedish recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Keep potato strip in cold water to prevent discoloration. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet and add onions.
Cook until soft, but not brown, about 5 minutes.
Pat potatoes dry.
Arrange layers of potatoes, onions and anchovies in greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Begin and end with potatoes.
Dot casserole with butter and sprinkle with pepper and bread crumbs.
Pour cream around the casserole.
Bake in the center of the oven until the potatoes are tender and most of the liquid is absorbed, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: sweet potatoes with caramel
directions: Cook the ingredients until makes syrup.
Put potatoes in dish; sprinkle with pecans.
Pour syrup mixture over all.

title: banana cherry bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs; add bananas, then flour and baking soda.
Stir in cherries and nuts by hand.
Pour in 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Combine with broccoli, cheese, bacon and onion.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Cook over low heat until thick and clear (10 minutes).
Color with red food coloring.
Add sliced strawberries when cool.
Pour on cake.

title: tennessee baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Saute onion in bacon grease until translucent.
Add beans, brown sugar, chili sauce and bacon.
Stir.
Pour in casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour over vegetables and chill.
Drain to serve.

title: tuna salad
directions: Thoroughly mix together all ingredients.
Serve on a lettuce leaf with crackers or use as a sandwich filling.

title: hot roll mix
directions: Put warm water into a bowl; add egg, salt, Crisco and sugar and dissolve well.
Make sure mixture is warm.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in the warm water for about 3 minutes.
Add flour a small amount at a time; mix well.
Let set 5 minutes.
Put on floured board or table on wax paper and knead.
Make into rolls; let rise about 25 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until done.
Brush with melted butter.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground sausage and hamburger meat together; add onion to the meat while cooking.
Drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese in a crock-pot.
Add the remaining ingredients and the cooked meat to the melted cheese.
Mix well.
Serve hot.

title: kielbasa, onion and potato scallop
directions: In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, mix potatoes, sauce mix, boiling water, butter and milk.
Stir in onions; place sausage on top.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 30 to 35 minutes, until potatoes are fork-tender.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces. Slice strawberries. Using a clear glass bowl, layer cake, strawberries and Cool Whip. The last layer should be Cool Whip.
